title: savory chicken enchilada bake
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender. Stir in flour, water and bouillon; cook and stir until thickened and bouillon melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup sauce, chicken, 1 cup cheese, chilies and chili powder; mix well.
Dip each tortilla into remaining hot sauce to soften.
Fill each with equal portions of chicken mixture.
Roll up and turn over in pan.
Use lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spoon remaining sauce over enchiladas. Sprinkle remaining cheese and any leftover sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream powdered sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly. Cook the other ingredients together until thick, then cool. Sprinkle 2/3 of crumbs in shell.
Pour cooled pudding over crumbs. Add whipped cream and top with rest of crumbs.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Spread pie filling into oiled pan.
In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend in softened margarine and egg, stirring to make thick batter.
Drop batter from spoon to cover pie filling.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is brown.
May also substitute cherry pie filling.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and then sweeten to taste.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove	stems;	chop.
Mix
ingredients and stuff mushrooms. Place
in buttered pan and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: company rice
directions: Mix together in a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole.
Spread sweet orange marmalade on top. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix cherry and strawberry Jell-O together.
Add 2 cups boiling water and Coca-Cola.
Refrigerate until it congeals a little.
Add drained pineapple, drained cherries and chopped nuts.
Finish congealing in refrigerator.
Serve in glass bowl (too pretty to hide).

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake as many muffins as desired at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be stored for 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: icing for fruit cake
directions: Bring to a hard boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 2 teaspoons of vanilla.
Pour on hot cake.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: cinnamon tortillas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush tortillas with water.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Mix well and shape with hands into size desired.
Drop on well-greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Chop onions and ham.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Mix the flour, butter and powdered sugar. Press
in	ungreased
square
pan	(8
x
8 x 2-inch), building up 1/2 inch on edges.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Fruit should be chilled and drained before mixing for quick serving.
This salad may be prepared ahead of time and chilled.

title: chocolate oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
In large mixing bowl, beat shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs; blend well.
Stir in together flour, cocoa, soda and salt; also cinnamon.
Add alternately with milk to shortening mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Gradually stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove; cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet onto a wire rack to cool.
Yield: about 5 dozen.
Very good.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in greased iron skillet.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Combine all wet ingredients with egg.
Combine dry ingredients and add to wet.
Add liquid if necesary to moisten.
Stiff bird and roast.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Grate cheese and chop onion.
In saucepan, heat soups and tomato sauce until smooth and heated through.
Do not boil.

title: herb-sour cream stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks; add sour cream and remaining ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Spoon or pipe into egg whites.
Garnish, if desired.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together Miracle Whip, half and half, mustard, vinegar, sugar, onion, hard-boiled eggs and celery.
Mix together with potatoes and cool.
Very good!!

title: peanut butter, pecans and bacon
directions: Cut bacon strips into thirds.
Spread peanut butter on pecans and roll in bacon strips.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Makes 54 (approximately).

title: sour cream salad
directions: Drain all fruit and mix into sour cream; add pecans. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt chocolate over low heat.
Add sugar, milk and salt and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until ingredients are dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until mixture reaches soft ball stage or 234° on thermometer.
Remove from heat and let stand without stirring until lukewarm or 110°.
Add butter and vanilla and beat until mixture is thick and loses glaze.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: wacky cocoa cake
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Really moist!!

title: lobster
directions: Plunge lobster into boiling water to cover; remove.
Place salt, 1 cup water, cooking rack and lobster into pressure cooker. Close cover securely and place regulator on vent pipe.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Cool pressure at once.
Plunge lobster into cold water; remove.
Crack shell.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: fried drumsticks
directions: Put drumsticks in bowl.
Pour buttermilk over and turn to coat each piece.
Marinate in refrigerator an hour.
Combine dry ingredients in plastic bag.
Add drumsticks and shake until coated.
Melt shortening in electric fryer on medium-high heat. Add drumsticks and cook until lightly browned, turning frequently. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 20 minutes, turning frequently.
Remove cover.
Cook on medium-high heat for 3 minutes to get crisp.
Drain on paper towels.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, Velveeta cheese and butter.
Heat until all cheese is melted.
Add 1 box of broccoli (let thaw until crumbly). Add green pepper, onion and Minute rice.
Mix together in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: honeyed chicken with oranges
directions: Peel and slice oranges.
Cut slices into 4 wedges; set aside. Cut chicken into 3/4-inch pieces.
Heat oil in wok over high heat. Add chicken pieces; stir-fry over medium heat until firm and white, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add orange juice, honey, hot pepper sauce and ginger, if desired.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Stir into chicken mixture until thickened, 30 to 60 seconds.
Add orange wedges.
Stir until hot.
Serve over rice.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease dish (10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inches). Slightly cook broccoli.
Layer chicken and broccoli in dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Arrange cheese slices on top of soup mixture.

title: chess pies
directions: Press pie dough into muffin tins and fill with mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cake(rich and moist)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour water over oats and let stand 20 minutes. Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add oats and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. While warm, spread with icing.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place a layer of potatoes in a buttered baking dish.
Add some minced onion and parsley.
Sprinkle with some salt, pepper and flour and dot with butter.
Repeat until all ingredients are used. Pour hot milk over potatoes and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: john marzetti
directions: Brown ground beef. Add chopped green pepper and onion and simmer for 10 minutes. Add tomatoes and simmer for 5 minutes. Add cream of mushroom soup and simmer for 3 minutes. Pour over cooked, drained noodles. Chop cheese and melt into this.

title: john's tequila chicken chili
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add garlic, onion, chili powder, cumin seed, chili flakes and coriander; saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken meat cut into rough chunks.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except masa, rice, cilantro sprigs and lime wedges.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat slightly and simmer, stirring occasionally, until mixture is fairly thick but still slightly liquid, about 1 1/4 hours.
Sprinkle in masa; stir and simmer until thick, about 15 minutes more.
Serve over steamed rice; garnish with cilantro sprigs and lime wedges.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and butter; blend well.
Pack firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs, vanilla and remaining sugar; beat until fluffy. Spread over crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Combine blueberry pie filling, lemon rind and lemon juice in a saucepan.
Place over low heat; bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Spread over cheesecake; chill.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat Hormel chili and cheese over medium heat, stirring until cheese melts and mixture is hot.
Add hot sauce and garlic salt. Serve warm with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
Heat butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms to skillet.
Cook slowly, occasionally turning until brown.
Makes 2 servings.

title: carrot bread
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Line loaf pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss together and set aside.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Blend together the cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk; set aside.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: Combine chocolate and sweetened condensed milk.
Heat the mixture on top of the stove or in the microwave, stirring frequently, just until the chocolate is melted and the mixture can be thoroughly combined.
Remove the chocolate from the heat and stir in your choice of nuts, raisins or cereal.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Line large cookie sheet with foil.
Spray with Pam.
Lay crackers on cookie sheet.
Melt butter over medium heat; add brown sugar.
Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute only.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Pour mixture over crackers and spread with spatula so all crackers are covered.
Bake no longer than 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits. Spread to cover crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Let cool until set.

title: date delights
directions: Heat sugar and margarine until mixture boils, then remove from stove and add beaten egg.
Return to stove and add chopped dates. Boil until mushy.
Remove from stove and add crushed vanilla wafers, vanilla and enough coconut to make a firm mix.
Press into dish and sprinkle with a small amount of coconut.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt Velveeta and butter in double boiler.
Remove from heat and add half and half.
Place potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add sauce mixture; place in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
No need to cover.

title: colored popcorn balls
directions: In medium saucepan over medium-low heat, melt margarine; add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Blend in dry Jell-O.
Mix well.
Pour over popped corn.
Mix well with buttered hands.
Form into balls; place on waxed paper.

title: russian cream fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until partially set. Fold in pineapple and juice, peaches, coconut and sour cream. Garnish with peach slices.

title: broccoli bacon quiche(crustless)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; set aside on a paper towel.
Beat eggs with cream, salt, garlic and lemon pepper.
Add cheese and broccoli; stir well.
Crumble 1/2 of bacon; stir into mixture. Fold in 1/2 of tomatoes.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with remaining tomatoes and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with crusty bread and green salad.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Make sauce and add cut up chicken.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Stir and bake 30 to 45 minutes more.

title: beef and beans
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper; drain.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange honey butter
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and process at high until smooth.
Spread on hot toast or muffins.
Yields about 1/2 cup.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Bake one hour at 375 degrees.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump undrained pineapple into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread in even layer. Sprinkle dry cake mix over cherry layer.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Put butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes. Serve warm or cool with whipped cream.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix everything together, then shape into rods (resembling your finger).
Bake until bottom is lightly browned, then roll them into the sugar mixture.
Set to cool on rack and roll again.

title: russian tea
directions: In one pot mix first four ingredients.
Heat and mix well. In second pot, mix next 2 ingredients.
Let come to a boil. Remove tea bags. Then add other ingredients with all ingredients. Mix all together.
Heat and serve.

title: quick butterscotch cream cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. On low speed, beat in water and pudding mix until smooth. Fold in half of the whipped topping and pour into crust. Chill 2 hours or until set. Garnish with remaining whipped topping and serve. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: dirty rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a covered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after the first 1/2 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the hamburger meat and drain.
Mix together in a large bowl:
lettuce, hamburger meat, 3 medium tomatoes (diced), 1 bag chips (broken up), shredded cheese, 1 small chopped onion (optional) and 1 large bottle Catalina salad dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain blueberries, cherries and pineapple.
Measure the liquid you drained and save. Add enough water to equal 1 cup.
Add this to the gelatin mixture. Stir in blueberries, cherries and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart flat pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: beef and lettuce packets
directions: In a large skillet, combine water, bouillon and horseradish. Bring to a boil. Add vegetables. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add beef; mix well. Place equal portions of beef mixture on lettuce leaves. Top with sprouts, tomatoes and desired salad dressing; roll up. Secure with wooden pick.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn delight
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: poultry pan gravy
directions: Strain juices from roasted poultry into measuring cup. Reserve 1/4 cup of fat and pan juices; discard the rest of fat.
In saucepan, heat the 1/4 cup fat and stir in the flour until blended.
Combine poultry stock with pan juices to make 2 cups. Slowly stir in juices to the blended flour, stirring constantly to avoid lumping.
Cook and stir gravy until smooth and simmer 5 minutes.
Add cooked chopped giblets.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grate corn from ear.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Cook slowly in baking dish until it thickens.
Brown at 350°.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Add bouillon cube, boiling water, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar, pineapple and syrup, peppers and onions. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove chops to heated platter.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir in liquid, cook stirring constantly until mixture is thick and clear.
Serve over chops.

title: speedy ravioli bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a large saucepan, cook ravioli to desired doneness as directed on package; drain.
Set aside.

title: pop pop's shrimp casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Saute onions and celery in butter.
Pour soup over potatoes.
Add celery and onion, then pimento and shrimp.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly, about 45 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: seven up salad
directions: Heat applesauce in sauce pan;
Sprinkle jello over the applesauce.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Add Seven Up.
Chill until jello sets.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until well blended.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil the brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and water.
Add the bottle of barbecue sauce and the bottle of tomato ketchup.
Simmer.
Pour over previously cooked beef or pork (cut in small bits) and let simmer a few minutes.
Good on buns. (This is good over leftover roast cut in small bits.)

title: frozen punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients.
This makes 2 gallons.
This punch may be frozen.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and shortening.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Roll into 2 logs.
Let stand overnight.
Slice and bake.

title: homemade windex
directions: Use 1 tablespoonful of ammonia to 1 quart of water.
Keep it in a quart jar with the lid screwed on.
Use it in a spray bottle.
It is just as good as any Windex you buy.

title: cherry salad or cherry dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 1 hour.

title: coffee drop cookies
directions: Stew raisins with water and let get cold.
Cream sugars and shortening; add eggs and beat.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and spices.
Add about 1/2 cup flour mixture and beat, then coffee. Add raisins before last 1/4 of flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 62 to 65 cookies.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and dry sweet potatoes.
Rub a little grease over the skins.
Bake until tender in a 425° oven for 30 to 60 minutes, depending on the size of potatoes.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Chop cabbage.
Cook 10 minutes in salt water; drain.
Mix all together in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Heat milk, soup and cheese until cheese is melted.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, celery, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, soup and milk: heat.
Mix tuna and noodles into mixture, pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar until creamy.
Lay cream cheese out to get room temperature.
Mix with marshmallow cream.
Add Jell-O (dry).

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
When done, top with more barbecue sauce if desired.

title: scaloppine al limone(sauteed veal or chicken with lemon)
directions: Season scallops with salt and pepper. Coat with flour.
Melt butter in 10 to 12 inch skillet over moderate heat.
Add oil. Saute scallops for about 2 minutes on each side (until golden). Transfer scallops to platter. Pour off most of fat leaving just a film.
Add 1/2 cup beef stock.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Return scallops to pan. Arrange lemon slices on top. Cover pan and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Lay peaches in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make a thick batter from next 6 ingredients.
Spread batter over peaches.
Mix together flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over batter, then pour boiling water over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: molded carrot salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on package.
Season vegetables with salt, pepper and vinegar.
Allow jello to partly thicken.
Add vegetables and mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: dream pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and press in bottom of pan.
Fix pudding as directions on box.
Then add Eagle Brand milk and 1 Cool Whip. Mix well together, then pour mixture over crushed cookies.
Then cover top with the other Cool Whip and grate a Hershey bar on top of Cool Whip.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: corn recipe
directions: Mix ingredients and heat until cheese is melted at 325°.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind the first 5 ingredients and mix.
Boil 5 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to mix.
Boil 5 minutes more.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 11 pints.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and heat over low heat.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Cream margarine, Sugar Twin and egg in a bowl.
Mix in applesauce and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg together in a large bowl.
Combine contents of both bowls and beat well.
Fold in raisins and oatmeal. Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto prepared sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until firm.
Yield:
42 cookies.
Calories:
112 per 2 cookies. Carbohydrates:
15 gm.
Sodium:
96 mg.
Fat:
5 gm.
Cholesterol: 13 mg.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan (set aside 1/2 cup for top).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together.
Pour in pan.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon butter; spread over mixture and chill.

title: turkey strata
directions: In 2-quart saucepan in hot butter, cook onion with rosemary until onion is tender.
Stir in gravy, eggs, milk and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Reserve 12 bread triangles.
Lightly butter 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/2 of the remaining bread and 1/2 of the remaining ingredients.
Repeat layers; top with reserved 12 bread triangles.
Pour egg mix over all; sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and set.

title: banana oat bran muffins(makes 15 to 18 muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray muffin tins with Pam spray. Combine dry ingredients, then add milk, Kroger Break-free egg product, honey and oil.
Mix until just moistened.
Add raisins, bananas and nuts (if desired).
Fill sprayed muffin tins.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar if desired.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: white punch
directions: Thaw lemon juice. Combine lemon juice, pineapple, grapefruit, sugar and water. Chill well.
Pour into punch bowl. Add ginger ale. Add ice cream. Float ice ring in bowl.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake
in
a Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: apple pear salad
directions: In a bowl, toss apples, pears and lemon juice. Add grapes and toss gently. In another bowl, combine water, vinegar, oil, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour over fruit and toss to coat.

title: chicken-tortellini soup
directions: Cook garlic in margarine over medium heat.
Add broth, then tortellini.
Heat to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach and other vegetables.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes more.
Serve with grated cheese and crusty bread.

title: mama's pear chip preserves
directions: Boil 30 minutes, covered.
Remove lid and boil, uncovered, until mixture turns red and syrup thickens.
Put in clean, sterilized jars and seal.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute ingredients together.
Cook ground beef, chopped onion, garlic and bell pepper in skillet.
When cooked, remove from fire and add to cooked rice.
Stir until well mixed, along with chicken liver.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
After ground beef mixture is cooked, add to bean mixture.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix well and pour into muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 - 20 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix leek soup mix, sour cream, mayo, spinach and water chestnuts.
Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Tear out middle of pumpernickel bread.
Put pieces on tray around loaf. Fill bread with dip.
Serve.

title: the best chicken noodle soup you've ever tasted
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Place in a kettle and cover with water.
Add salt and small bunch of parsley tied with a string.
In a piece of cheesecloth, add rest of ingredients and tie together and add to chicken and water.
Simmer slowly about 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Skim off fat and remove spices and parsley greens.
Cook noodles separately.
Add to chicken and broth.

title: fruit pizza(makes 1 pizza pan)
directions: Set oven to 325°.
Mix together all ingredients and pat in a lightly greased pizza pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm buttermilk; set aside.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Cut margarine into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk-yeast mixture; stir until well blended.
Knead and roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Spray pan with Pam.
Place biscuits on baking pan so they are touching each other.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Place another biscuit on top of buttered biscuit.
Brush top with butter.
Let rise at room temperature 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar and flour; beat in thoroughly eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in nuts.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: diabetic date cake
directions: Cream margarine; add egg, sweetener and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture along with applesauce.
Blend well.
Add dates and pecans.
Turn into loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
May also be baked as sheet cake.
Adjust time for sheet cake.

title: swiss steak
directions: Place steak onto a double piece of aluminum foil.
Place remaining ingredients over meat.
Securely wrap foil around meat and fixings; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mocha torte
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix and press in pie plate. Bake at 300° until brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Recipe can be cut in half if necessary.)

title: dill dip
directions: Blend and chill at least 2 hours.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with raw vegetables.
(May use low-fat mayonnaise and sour cream.)

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In large frypan, stir and break up beef in oil for 1 minute. Add onion, salt, pepper and rice.
Mix well while sauteing for 2 to 3 minutes.
Then add soup and water.
Mix well.
Turn cabbage into greased casserole.
Pour mixture evenly over raw cabbage. (Do not stir.)
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Chill and serve in 1 hour.

title: noodles stroganoff
directions: Cook onions, mushrooms and garlic in butter.
Add beef; cook until brown.
Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper and mix in.
Add consomme, tomato paste and vinegar.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Blend in sour cream and parsley.
Heat.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: mexican wedding cakes(cookies)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Blend in salt, vanilla and flour.
Mixture is stiff.
Pinch off small pieces of dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: dirt cake
directions: Break up cookies; place in blender until dirt like.
Set aside.

title: ethel's sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together; blend in.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with 3-inch cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until cookies are a delicate golden color.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Melt shortening or oil, add beef and brown slowly.
Add onions, garlic, green pepper, celery, pimentos, consomme, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch blended with water and soy sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: dameon's tacos
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper; drain grease.
Layer meat, cheese and lettuce in shell and top with sauce.

title: squash dressing
directions: Add the baking powder to the cornbread mix and prepare as directed on package.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add squash, onion and pepper.
Saute until tender.
Transfer to casserole dish and add all other ingredients.
Crumble cornbread and add, stirring slightly.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: mimi's jam cake
directions: Strawberry jam may be used.
Bake in three layers at 325° for 45 minutes or until sides turn loose and springs back to touch.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix together (except chocolate) and shape into eggs.
Then dip in chocolate.
Makes about 40 eggs.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Brown meat and then
place
it
in bottom of 2 1/2 quart baking dish.
Top
with
onions
and potatoes, salt and pepper. Mix soup and milk;
pour
over
top
of other mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour; top with cheese and melt if desired.

title: texas hash
directions: Fry onion, pepper and meat until mixture falls apart.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 2-quart dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple pudding
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Add rest of ingredients. Fold in apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scottish shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix sugars and flour.
Mix the butter pieces with the flour mixture in a large plastic bag.
Knead lightly until dough holds together.
Remove from bag.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Flatten each cookie with a cookie press, fork or the bottom of a glass.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes (or until pale golden).
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen, depending on size.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet; drain fat.
In an oblong baking dish, layer meat and onions, soup and cheese, then top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until Tater Tots are brown.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar and water, without stirring, until it spins a thread when a little is dropped in water.
Pour slowly into the stiffly beaten egg white.
Beat until thick.
Add vanilla and drop from spoon onto wax paper.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts or place 1 nut on each piece.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small meatballs. Place in pan and bake for about 1 1/2 hours.
Then remove from oven and drain off excess grease.
Bake at 350°.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water. Cool. Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each. Blend in vanilla and chocolate. Sift flour after each addition until smooth. Fold in beaten whites. Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.

title: peach and blueberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, put fruit and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix sugar, tapioca and salt.
Toss lightly into fruit.
Let stand 15 minutes, then pour into pie crust, mounding in the center. Cover with top crust, folding edges under each other to seal.
Make 4 slits in the top of the crust.
Brush top with egg yolk and water mixture.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: #20 jelly meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients except chili sauce and grape jelly.
Shape mixture into meatballs about 1 inch thick.
Brown meatballs and remove fat.
Place jelly and chili sauce in skillet.
Stir until melted and add meatballs.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix yeast, warm water, sugar and salt.
Add eggs.
Mix oil with boiling water.
Add to first mixture.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Let rise 1 hour.
Mash.
Pinch off and roll in melted butter.
Can put in loaf pan or cake pan.
Let rise 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: light brownies
directions: Omit 2 eggs and 1/2 cup oil from recipe directions on box of brownies.

title: jan's potluck corn
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook chicken until done and remove skin and bones.
Tear into small pieces.
In skillet, melt butter and add chopped onion, celery and bell pepper, cooking until tender.
In boiler, add chicken broth left from chicken, then add the two soups, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce and cook until blended.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: diet cranberry sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in large saucepan; heat to boiling, stirring often.
Boil rapidly until berries all pop open (5 to 10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: mince meat cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour. Do not overbake.
Let stand for a while in pan.
Grease and line pan with wax paper.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Combine all ingredients except zucchini; beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.
Let stand 10 minutes; cut into squares.
Serve warm.

title: pork casserole
directions: Braise cutlets on top of stove.
Put in bottom of baking dish, then add medium sliced potatoes, then carrots and onions on top. Add Prego sauce, a little water, salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain grease, then add other ingredients.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix well; pour in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break bread into pieces and put bread into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs; add mustard, salt and milk.
Mix and pour over the bread crumbs.
Spread shredded cheese over all; cover tightly with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next day in a 325° oven for one hour.

title: chicken chile casserole
directions: Combine chicken with chiles, onion and soup.
Spread tortillas with butter, then cut in half.
Arrange 6 tortilla halves in buttered 13 x 9-inch shallow baking pan.
Cover with 1/3 of chicken mixture and sprinkle with 1/3 of shredded cheese.
Repeat layers twice.
Pour chicken broth over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove foil about last 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mocha walnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 cup chocolate chips (over hot water or in microwave).
Stir until smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Dissolve coffee in boiling water; set aside.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In medium bowl mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well with a spoon.
Gradually add flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt, beating until well blended.
Stir in chips.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Reserve trunk to store pieces in.
Add enough gravy to cover.
Cook over fire about 4 weeks.
This serves 3,800 people. If more are expected, more rabbits may be added.
Use only as necessary.
People do not like to find hare in their stew.
If elephant does not suit your taste, substitute donkey.

title: chocolate muffins(roger's favorite)
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add everything to it and mix. Pour into muffin pans and bake at 350° for 20 minutes (they don't look quite done when ready to come out).

title: snickers ice cream
directions: Chop Snickers into small pieces.
With a mixer, beat eggs until foamy.
Mix in sugar.
Add Pet milk, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Pour into freezer.
Add additional sweet milk to fill line on freezer.

title: creamy ambrosia salad
directions: Drain diced oranges.
Combine oranges with next 3 ingredients; chill.
Fold dessert topping into mayonnaise; fold into fruits.
Spoon into crisp lettuce cups; sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked chicken wings
directions: Defrost chicken wings and rinse in cold water; pat dry. Combine all ingredients and marinate for 24 hours. Discard marinade and bake wings in single layer at 350° for about 1 hour. Serve with duck sauce, if desired.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo and cool; add beaten eggs, lemon juice, sugar and salt to melted oleo.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut, raisins and pecans.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 30 or 40 minutes in 325° oven.
This freezes well.
Great with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cook squash covered in boiling water until tender; drain.
Mash enough to fill one cup; save remainder.
Combine the one cup mashed squash with eggs; stir well.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Stir well.
Add squash mixture; add onion.
Stir well until blended.
Drop mixture by tablespoon into hot oil until well browned.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Boil macaroni according to package for 7 minutes; drain. Add macaroni, eggs, half and half and cubed Velveeta cheese together in a greased casserole dish. Mix sharp and Monterey cheeses together. Add 1 1/2 cups of cheese to macaroni. Put 1/2 cup aside. Salt and pepper to taste. Top with 1/2 cup cheese and dabs of butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Break egg into a 1-quart jar with lid.
Stir with scraper.
Add milk and 1 tablespoon of oil.
Screw lid on tightly.
Shake to mix well.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into jar. Close lid tightly.
Shake to mix well.
Batter should have some lumps.
Turn burner on medium heat; rub a little cooking oil on griddle with a paper towel.
Heat griddle.
Measure 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
When bubbles cover surface of pancake and edges look dry, turn over.
Cook until golden brown.
Makes 7 or 8 pancakes.
Serve with syrup or fresh fruit.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand.
Mix all wet ingredients with the yeast; add the cooled oatmeal.
Add the dry ingredients and raisins; mix well.
Put into two greased loaf pans; let stand for 30 minutes to rise.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken taquitos
directions: Simmer chicken in water in 10-inch skillet, covered, 20 to
25 minutes.
Remove
from
water and cool.
Shred chicken with fork. Saute onion and garlic in one tablespoon oil for 1 to
2 minutes.
Stir
in chicken, tomatoes, chicken broth and spices. Simmer
to 5 minutes.
In a heavy 10-inch skillet, heat about 1-inch
of	oil.
Dip
tortillas in oil quickly to soften, drain on	paper
towels (reserve oil).
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of the
chicken
mixture
down the center of each tortilla.
Roll-up tortillas	tightly.
Secure
with	wooden toothpicks.
Fry rolled
up	tortillas
at
375° until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pepper hash
directions: Cut up peppers.
Cover with hot water and let set for 5 minutes.
Put peppers and all ingredients together.
Bring to boil on stove.
Pour hot hash into clean jars.

title: no-fail fudge
directions: Combine Milnot, margarine and sugar.
Heat in heavy saucepan until boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 6 minutes and remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until all ingredients are blended smoothly.
Pour into buttered 12 3/4 x 9-inch pan. Cover immediately with plastic wrap covering the fudge itself. Allow to cool and cut into squares.
Enjoy!

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Freeze until firm overnight or all day.
Serves 50.

title: taco pie
directions: Fry hamburger meat and add taco seasoning.
Line the bottom of a pie pan with the crescent rolls.
Bake until done.
Add ground beef, cheese, sour cream and crumbled Doritos.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: dumplings
directions: Cut butter into flour until it looks like coarse cornmeal. Add egg. Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients. Roll dough very thin and cut with pizza cutter into bite size pieces. Drop into hot chicken broth. Cook until they are tender.

title: corn and peppers
directions: Mix all the ingredients together; heat over stove until butter and cream cheese melt.
Put in oven at 250° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken blt salad
directions: Combine the chicken, bacon, lettuce and tomatoes.
Pour Ranch dressing over salad. I usually buy the pre-roasted chicken breasts.

title: chocolate cloud pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Spread over the white layer Cool.

title: mushroom fettucini
directions: In medium skillet, heat oil and add onions.
Saute until tender.
Add mushrooms, garlic, and basil.
Saute 2-3 minutes longer.
Stir in sour cream.
Add fettucini and toss to coat. Heat thoroughly (do not boil).
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: chocolate-pecan chess pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and vanilla and stir into sugar mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Cook stew beef until tender.
Mix all soups and milk together. Place cooked, drained beef into 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish; top with soups.
Bake at 300° approximately 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Top noodles with baked beef/soups.
Mix thoroughly.

title: after church stew
directions: Chop beef into 1/2 inch cubes (chuck, round, or sirloin).

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, pecans, corn syrup and water in a large Dutch oven.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan.
Uncover and cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches hard crack stage (300°). Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, orange rind, soda and extract.

title: cheesy spinach party loaf
directions: Note:
May add 1/3 cup each chopped celery and green pepper (optional).

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except Hershey's Kisses.
Use rounded teaspoonful of dough. Shape into balls. Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Take out of oven and put Kiss on them.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Drain & rinse vegetables. Mix ingredients. Season with bacon grease. Salt & pepper. Cook 2 hours in crockpot.

title: monal schnitz
directions: Mix sugar and ground almonds; save 1/2 cup for topping.
Beat in egg yolks, egg white and almond or vanilla extract.
Add flour and baking powder. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: polvorones de canele(cinnamon cookies)
directions: Cream 1/2 cup + 1 tsp. confectioners' sugar and butter or margarine together.
Add 1/2 tsp. cinnamon, salt and vanilla. Stir in flour making a stiff dough.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Mix together 1 cup confectioners' sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon. Roll in cinnamon mixture.
Bake
for 15 to 20 minutes, until nicely browned. Cool cookies on rack.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sesame buttered beans
directions: In a heavy saucepan, toast sesame seed.
Add butter; melt. Stir in remaining ingredients; cook over medium heat until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fried okra
directions: Thoroughly wash and drain okra.
Trim tops and tails; slice in 3/8-inch pieces.
Toss in mixture of corn meal, salt and pepper. Fry in hot bacon fat until crisp and golden brown; drain on paper towels.
This is grand as a side dish.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In a covered pan, cook cabbage in small amount of boiling water without seasoning for 12 minutes or until tender.
Drain. In large skillet, cook celery in butter until brown; pour in milk and cheese.
Stir until mixture is thick (on low heat).
Then put in cabbage and season.
Put into baking dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: winter cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and onion.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, water, vinegar and salt in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until almost boiling.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into eggs.
Pour egg mixture into the rest of the mixture and cool over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in bacon.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture.
Toss well.

title: pizza crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk and stir.
Knead in more flour until it can be handled easily.
Spread 1/2 of the dough onto greased and floured pizza pan.

title: chocolate passion dessert
directions: Bake brownies as directed on package and cut into 24 squares. In a 3-quart serving bowl (clear bowl, if available), layer 2 brownie squares, 1 cup of strawberries and 1 banana, sliced.
Cover with 1 tub of chocolate Cool Whip.
Repeat same layering process with remaining brownies, strawberries, bananas and chocolate Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: creole stuffed peppers
directions: Split peppers in half. Clean out white veins.
Cook beef and onion.
Pour off fat.
Mix beef, rice and seasonings.
Add approximately 1/4 cup Creole Sauce.
Pack pepper halves with mixture and place in a large shallow baking dish.
Pour 3/4 cup sauce around peppers.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serve with 1/2 cup remaining sauce, heated over peppers.

title: babka
directions: Scald milk and butter.
Soak raisins in warm water.
Beat all eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla, orange rind, nutmeg and mace into egg and sugar mixture.
Take 3/4 cup lukewarm water, 1 tablespoon of flour and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Add yeast; mix and dissolve. Let rise to double its bulk.
Add milk into egg mixture.
Add flour (about 2 cups) with raised yeast.
Keep adding flour slowly and mixing.
Add drained raisins before last 2 cups of flour and beat well.
Let rise in pan to double in bulk, then fill pans and let rise about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour. Makes 3 in funnel cake pans or makes 5 in regular loaf pans.

title: cherry salad with coca-cola
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple and add water to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil and pour over gelatin; stir until dissolved.
When cool, add Coca-Cola, stir and chill until partly congealed.
Add drained cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.
Grate frozen cream cheese on top of mold. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer rice, broccoli and chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. To make sauce heat cream of chicken soup, celery soup, mayonnaise, margarine, lemon juice and curry.
Mix well and spread over chicken.
Top with cheese.
May sprinkle on sliced almonds if desired.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Flatten breasts or thighs between 2 sheets of plastic with a mallet or rolling pin.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Coat large skillet with vegetable spray and place over medium-high heat until hot.
Saute chicken for 8 minutes, turning once, until tender.
Transfer to platter and keep warm.
Wipe skillet with paper towel.
Add margarine, mushrooms and onion and saute.
Add flour and stir; add milk and stir until thick.
Add Parmesan and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Spoon over chicken.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Serves 6 with only 148 calories per serving.

title: pork chop scallop
directions: Grease a 10-inch skillet.
Add pork chops and brown on both sides.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove chops from skillet.
Empty potatoes and seasonings sauce mix into skillet. Stir pimento and ingredients called for in the package.
Heat all to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Place pork chops on top of potatoes. Cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain off grease. Add remaining ingredients to meat mixture. Simmer 15 minutes or so.
Serve over hamburger buns.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain beans and discard juice.
Mash beans with fork, leaving some chunks.
Add remaining ingredients, but reserve cheese.
Mix well and pour in 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve with nachos.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Cover and bake 1 hour at 400°.
Remove cover to brown.
Sprinkle with paprika or melt grated cheese on top.
Make 6 servings.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Whip the first 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Blend the cookies in blender.
In flowerpot, start with a layer of cookies, then a layer of pudding; finish with cookies.
Place flower in pot.

title: eggplant balls
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil and gently saute garlic until golden brown.
Add diced eggplant and the tablespoon of water and cover.
Reduce heat and gently steam until eggplant is very soft.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: In a 3-quart baking dish, melt the margarine in the oven.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.
Add the mixture to the melted margarine; mix well.
Top the batter with the fruit.
Bake the cobbler at 350° for 45 minutes or until the top is browned.
The batter will raise to the top.

title: fillet of haddock and dressing
directions: Mix crumbs and seasonings together; set aside.
Heat butter in saucepan; add scallops and lemon juice (do not boil).
Add this to bread crumbs.
Spread mixture on fish and pat down.
Put in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: special green bean casserole
directions: Mix
first
7 ingredients and start on high heat.
Turn to low heat and cook for at least 1 hour; drain well.
Stir in Cheez Whiz.
Put	in
baking
dish
and top with French fried onions. Bake until bubbly at 325°.	Serves 10.

title: creamy baked chicken breast
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch is good).
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine and spoon sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until chicken is done and crumbs are crispy.

title: hot yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar, oil and salt.
Add 3/4 cup hot water and mix well. Cool mixture to lukewarm temperature.
In separate bowl, soak yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
After yeast dissolves, mix with sugar mixture.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well.
Work remaining cup of flour into mixture.
After well blended, cover with moist cloth and let rise until doubles in size.
Roll dough into 2-inch balls and let double in size again.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Lay rolls flat on cookie sheet or 2 pizza pans.
Bake until light brown.
Mix together and spread on cooled rolls the remaining ingredients.
Press down and let set in the refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.

title: french style herbed cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well until well blended.
Chill; serve with crusty French bread or crackers.

title: oven stew
directions: Brown meat in skillet (or roast as usual).
Use large roaster or pot with cover. Cube meat and place on bottom of roaster. Layer potatoes (leave whole) and carrots (leave whole). Cube onions and celery.
Pour in the stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce over layered vegetables and meat.
Sprinkle McCormick stew mix over mixture. Add water to mixture.
Cook, covered, in oven 2 hours at 350°.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Melt butter; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush Oreos (save 1/2 cup to sprinkle on top).
Smash Oreos into melted butter.
Mix 8 ounces Cool Whip with cream cheese; spread over Oreos.
Mix pudding with milk and chill for 5 minutes, then spread over Cool Whip layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with Oreo crumbs.
Chill overnight.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Layer cabbage, pepper and onions.
Mix last 6 items; heat to boiling point.
Pour over cabbage, onions and pepper.
Cover.
Let refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Toss before serving.
This will keep a week or more.
You can use less oil.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add butter, juice and then beaten egg and rest of juice.
Cook until thick.
Cook and pour over diced pineapple and marshmallows.

title: jerk seasoning
directions: Yields 5 tablespoons.
Will hold in airtight container for 2 months.

title: mountain cherry pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
In mixing bowl, mix together all except cherries.
Pour on melted butter.
Add cherries in center of batter.
Bake at 325° until batter is done.
Batter will come to the top.
Any fruit may be used instead of the cherries.

title: puff ball donuts
directions: Beat the first five ingredients together until it's a stiff dough.
Place sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon in a bag.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry slow until brown and done; lift out of oil.
Drop the dough into a bag and shake.

title: smoochies
directions: Mix ingredients and roll in balls (about a teaspoonful). Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: birthday cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pans.
Put flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda in bowl and mix until blended.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and water.
Mix until smooth.
Divide into pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Frost with whipped topping.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti in chicken broth. Don't drain. Melt margarine in a skillet and saut the chopped onion, green pepper and celery until tender. Add cheese and soups and stir until cheese melts and mixture is smooth. Pour mixture on top of spaghetti and broth. Add chicken and stir well. Spray 2 large casserole dishes with Pam. Divide mixture into dishes. Bake one and freeze the other one. Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 20 to 30 minutes). Cover with foil during baking. Near the end of baking time, remove the foil and sprinkle the top with shredded cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in small pan with about an inch of water.
Mix the first 4 ingredients with slices of cheese added.
Put broccoli in bottom of dish and pour 1/2 of mixture over it.
Cover this layer with slices of cheese.
Pour remaining mixture over the cheese layer and top with crumbled crackers.
Dot butter in several places on the cracker layer.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: calzones
directions: Note:
Any kind of meat or cheese can be used.

title: copper dollars
directions: Peel and slice carrots in 1/4-inch thick slices and place in saucepan.
Add water, cover and cook until tender.
Drain and cool. Slice and separate onions into rings.
Cut green pepper into strips.
Combine carrots, onions and peppers into bowl.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Put raisins, water, salt, sugar, Crisco and cinnamon in pan and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add baking soda and flour; add nuts and, if desired, mixed fruit.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan or floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine fruits.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; chill.
Fold whipped cream into mayonnaise.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Serve on lettuce lined plates.
Top with flaked coconut.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Combine mixed fruit, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Mix together vanilla pudding, Tang and juice from pineapple.
Pour over fruit and stir.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pesto dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender.
Top with cover. Process until smooth.
Pour into bowl.
Cover.
Chill. Serve with spinach salad.

title: gumbo(southern style)
directions: Slowly boil hen and ham hock together in 3 quarts water.
When done take out chicken.
Let cool; cut up breast in diced pieces. (Remove ham hock from stock.)
Fry large slice of ham; cut in very small pieces.
Skim off all fat from stock.
Fry onion light brown; pour tomatoes into skillet with onion.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add to stock.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put tomatoes, diced chicken and finely cut ham in stock; let cook slowly.
Add pint of chopped oysters (or same amount of crab meat or shrimp, finely cut), okra and flour thickening.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: cheeseball
directions: Drain pineapple juice.
Mix ingredients together with 1/2 cup nuts.
Then mold into a ball and roll in remaining nuts. Refrigerate.

title: 4 pasta beef bake
directions: Cook pasta. Cook beef, onion, pepper and mushrooms until beef no longer is pink (drain).

title: old ardfarkles original blue cheese dressing
directions: Into a 3 gallon bucket, put buttermilk and sour cream.
Mix together with electric mixer.
Crumble Blue cheese into mixture. Add Worcestershire and dill.
Add gallon of mayonnaise last. Blend well.
Chill.
Serves all of town.

title: pioneer gingersnap pie crust
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients and blend well.
Pat firmly into bottom and sides of 9-inch pan.
Fill with Aunt Mae's Pumpkin Chiffon.
Chill and enjoy!

title: chip chocolate angel food cake
directions: Make batter for angel food cake as directed, except at the last, fold in 1 square unsweetened chocolate (1 ounce), grated. Serve wedges of cake with ice cream and Glossy Chocolate Sauce. Or frost cake with Chocolate Butter Icing.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with crabmeat.
Put in small casserole; sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Serve with crackers.

title: sauerkraut salad(i got this at work years ago from a fellow co-worker.)
directions: Mix well with a fork.
Let stand 6 hours or overnight.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and juice from oranges.
After mixed well, fold in the oranges so as not to mash them.
Pour into 3 round 8 inch cake pans that have been sprayed and sprinkled with sugar.
Bake 350 degrees for 19 - 20 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: applesauce pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, applesauce, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Scald the milk.
Add 1/2 cup cream.
Mix well with pumpkin mixture.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool.
Whip 1/2 cup cream for the top.

title: ladyfingers cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Beat yolks until thick.
Fold into egg whites, then fold in vanilla, flour and salt.
Shape into 4 1/2-inch fingers on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with additional sugar and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Press together in pairs.

title: layered orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup orange juice for 1 minute.
Stir into boiling water.
Add sweetener and stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Stir in juices (3 cups orange juice and lemon).
Pour enough mixture to cover 1/2 to 1 inch of mold.
This becomes the clear top layer.
Chill until firm.
Chill larger amount of gelatin mixture until slightly thickened, then fold grapes and orange into this thickened mixture.
This will be the last to go into mold.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soups, vegetables, chicken, milk and spices.
Spoon into prepared pie crust, cover with top pie crust; crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: simple peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter with sugar and egg.
Then roll into 1-inch balls and put on a cookie sheet.
Press with a fork.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken dip
directions: Cook chicken and shred. Drain Ro-tel. In a bowl, mix chicken, sour cream, mayo, Ro-Tel, and cheese. Make ahead and chill. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: angu(cornmeal mush)
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan.
Cook the garlic and onion over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until soft but not brown. Add 2 cups water and bring to a rapid boil.

title: jellied waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into a 5-cup mold.
Chill overnight.
Unmold.
Serve with salad greens and mayonnaise, thinned with cream or honey. Yields 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: lasagna toss
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef, onions and garlic powder. Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, simmer to heat.
Remove 1 cup spaghetti sauce mix, set aside.
Stir cooked noodles into remaining sauce.
Place 1/2 noodle mix in casserole dish.
Cover with cottage cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining noodle mix, top with 1 cup of reserved meat sauce.
Add remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: In food processor fitted with steel blade, blend all ingredients, except milk.
Slowly add milk; blend 30 seconds. Pour into saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: cornbread(this recipe is good with ham and beans.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix milk and cornmeal.
Stir in beaten egg, then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and lightly floured pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
sugar
and well beaten eggs.
Add syrup, butter and vanilla
then
nuts.
Pour	into
unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes then reduce temperature to 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the cranberries, water and sugar. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, sprinkle the gelatin onto the orange juice to soften it and then add the gelatin-juice mixture to the hot cranberry mixture.
Cool the mixture, then chill it until it becomes syrupy (approximately 2 hours).
Fold in the celery, carrots, raisins and apples.
Pour mixture into serving dish.
Chill until mixture is firm (2 hours or more).

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Combine water, sugar and cherries.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Add pineapple (do not drain), nuts and Coke.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: dorothy's cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oats, coconut, nuts, dates and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Yields about 6 dozen cookies.

title: easy chili - macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix cooked macaroni, ground beef and all other ingredients (except cheese) in pan. Simmer on low 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Serve when melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine the ground beef, egg, 3/4 cup cereal, salt, pepper, green pepper and onion; mix well.
Mix together the sugar, catsup, nutmeg and mustard.
Add half of this sauce to the ground beef mixture; mix well.
Shape the meat mixture into 6 balls and place in 3-inch muffin cups.
Top the meatballs with the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 cup cereal.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a medium saucepan, then stir in the cream or half and half.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbling.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine or butter and vanilla.
Pour into the baked pastry shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in a 325° oven about 30 minutes or until the edge is bubbly.
Cool completely on a wire rack. Serves 8 to 10.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Beat in the eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, salt and baking soda; blend into the other mixture.
Add the candy bars.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove from sheets and cool.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: chewy cake
directions: Cake:
Beat one egg; melt oleo and mix egg and oleo to cake mix.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package instructions.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Enjoy!

title: buttery pull-apart bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Combine cheese, sesame seed and margarine. Coat each frozen roll in this mixture and place in pan.
Cover, thaw and rise overnight in refrigerator.
Then let stand at room temperature until completely risen, 2 to 4 hours.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake additional 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serves 12.

title: deviled crab
directions: In large bowl, toss crabmeat, cracker crumbs, celery, onion, parsley, red pepper (chopped), mustard, ground red pepper, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise.
Divide the mixture among six 1-cup custard cups.
Dot each with margarine and bake at 350° until the tops are golden, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with pepper rings and lemon slices.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk.
Chill one hour.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake at 450° for one hour (watch closely).

title: pastel dessert
directions: *For better flavor results, use the juice of the drained fruit to complete the whole 2 1/2 cups of liquid.

title: fudgsicles
directions: In saucepan, mix contents of pudding package with 4 cups evaporated milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to boil.
Pour into baking pan.
Freeze for 24 hours.
Cut into squares.
Stick a plastic spoon into each square and serve.

title: spicy caraway beef kabobs
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the water, lemon juice, soy sauce, ginger root, caraway seed, coriander, turmeric, red pepper and garlic.
Stir in the beef and onion.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 20 minutes, stirring once or twice. Drain the meat, reserving the marinade.
Thread the meat onto 4 metal skewers.
Place the kabobs on a grill rack.
Grill until the beef is cooked through, 10 to 15 minutes, turning the kabobs frequently.
Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, bring the reserved marinade to a boil.
Brush the marinade over the kabobs.
Serve the kabobs on top of the hot, cooked rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: two tone fudge
directions: Take one banana; peel.
Place on plate and put Hershey's syrup on it and Cool Whip on it and sprinkle a tiny pinch of sugar.
Eat with a fork!

title: grama's best macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Grease 2 quart casserole.
Slice cheese. Layer macaroni, butter and cheese.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Repeat layer 3 to 4 times.
Top layer should consist of cheese, flour and butter.
Pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix cream cheese (room temperature) with sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add milk to the desired texture.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer bowl in order of ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice. In a double boiler, melt butter. Add flour to make a paste. Add milk, cream cheese and salt until blended. Mix all ingredients together and put in 2-quart greased casserole. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: layered dip for corn chips
directions: 1st Layer:
Take two cans of bean dip and spread in Pyrex dish.

title: bacon casserole
directions: Separate dough; place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place cheese on top.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over cheese. Sprinkle with bacon and parsley.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Cool 5 or 10 minutes before serving.

title: bubble buns
directions: Grease 10 muffin pan cups.
In a small bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
Separate biscuits.
Cut into quarters.
Shape into balls.
Coat with mayo or Miracle Whip.
Roll in walnut mixture. Place 4 in each cup.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes, until brown.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Saute onions in margarine; stir in flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Place chicken in single layers in glass pan.
Pour sauce over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in mixture of salt and 1 tablespoon flour.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a hot skillet.
Add meat and quickly brown on all sides.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is barely tender.
Transfer skillet contents to a bowl and keep warm.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter to pan drippings. Blend in 3 tablespoons of flour and catsup.
Slowly add beef broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Return meat to pan and stir in sour cream.
Heat briefly.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Toss above ingredients, chill & serve.

title: sweet and sour ham balls(low-fat)
directions: In mixing bowl, combine egg, bran flakes, milk and ginger.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add meat and mix.
Shape into meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered; drain.
In saucepan, drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set both aside.
In a large saucepan, cook carrots in broth, covered, for 5 minutes or until just tender. Do not drain.
Combine vinegar, cornstarch, honey and soy sauce. Stir into carrot mixture.
Stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in pea pods and cook 2 minutes more.
Stir in pineapple; heat through.
Stir in meatballs. Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.
Very good.

title: spice 'n applesauce snack cake
directions: Prepare topping:
In small bowl, stir 1/2 cup packed brown sugar, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate pieces; spread over batter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients together and sprinkle with 5 tablespoons of table salt.
Mix and let set overnight.
In the morning, drain (do not rinse).
Bring remainder of ingredients to a boil.
Add vegetables and simmer about 1 hour.
Put in jars and seal.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; run into both sides of steak. Preheat skillet; add half of shortening, then add onions (sliced). Brown lightly and remove from skillet.
Add remaining shortening. Brown steak on both sides.
Reduce heat, add carrots, celery, garlic, tomatoes and water.
Cover, simmer 1 hour.
Cut pepper into slices.
Add onions and pepper to meat.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add chocolate and butter.
Combine milk and egg and add to mixture.
Cook very slowly, stirring constantly.
When thickened, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Pour filling into cooled pie shell.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat with onions and garlic in a medium saucepan.
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer gently 15 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups.

title: chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces.
Sprinkle with salt, garlic salt and paprika.
Place in one layer in Pyrex type dish.
Mix soup with cream and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine meat, water and soups in crock-pot.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Cook egg noodles as directed on package.
Top the noodles with the mixture.
May add sour cream to top of mixture.

title: mexi-quick
directions: Brown chuck and season with salt, chili powder and garlic. Put meat mixture in crock-pot.
Add soups and chilies.
Cook on high until heated thoroughly.
Turn to low until ready to serve. Add package of chips and serve immediately with extra chips.

title: peppakoka(swedish christmas cookies)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add beaten egg and Karo. Mix all dry ingredients together; add water.
Mix together. Chill overnight, covered with Saran Wrap.

title: (3) bean salad
directions: Drain 3 cans of beans and mix with oil, sugar and vinegar. Add chopped onion, pepper, pimiento, salt and pepper.
Let stand to absorb mixture.
I use home-canned beans.
Chill and serve.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on box.
Mix pasta, Ricotta cheese and sauce together.
Hold back approximately 1 cup sauce. Spread into a glass 9 x 12-inch casserole and level.
Pour remaining sauce over top and spread evenly.
Cover with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry skillet cookies
directions: In a skillet combine dates, coconut, sugar, margarine and egg. Cook, stirring until mixture bubbles and thickens.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Cool 10 minutes.
Shape in a strawberry shape; roll in red sugar crystals.
Trim with green frosting leaves.

title: corn bake
directions: Stir together and pour into baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Double recipe for long Pyrex dish.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water for about 10 minutes. Drain and mash. Combine soup and sour cream, then fold in squash mixture. Combine stuffing and butter. Put 1/2 in bottom of baking dish, then squash, then remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown flour to medium brown.
Add shrimp last.
Cook until shrimp turn pink.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add Wesson oil and blend well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Fold in grated carrots.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Yields 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: simple swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces and put in a crock-pot. Sprinkle with soup mix, salt and pepper.
Pour in tomatoes and cook for 6 to 8 hours on low.

title: green tomato pickle
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions.
Layer alternately, sprinkling each layer with canning salt.
Use a crock or closed vessel to place these layers and let set overnight.
Drain well and squeeze gently as you place in cooking vessel.
Cover with this mixture vinegar, pepper, allspice, dry mustard, cloves and celery seed.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: marie's very own hush puppies
directions: Bring water to boil with salt, onion powder and sugar.
Turn off electric burner.
Stir in corn meal vigorously.
Dip hands in water and roll out about 1 tablespoon at a time in cocoon shape. Deep fry.

title: zippy dip
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in margarine for 1 minute. Add beef and brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until thick over medium heat.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: columbian flank steak
directions: Grind or crush together all ingredients, except the meat.
Rub meat well with the mixture and refrigerate, covered, for 24 hours. Next day, place meat and marinade in pressure cooker with 5 cups water.
Cook under pressure about 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Place in a baking pan and brown in a hot oven, basting with its juice to avoid drying out.

title: best tomato soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter (do not brown).
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
(I don't like tomato soup, but I love this!)

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients.
Nuts are optional.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° in a Bundt pan for 1 hour or a long pan for 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: lisa west's uncooked non-hardening playdough
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Store in an airtight container.

title: fried rice and soy chicken
directions: In large frying pan, cook vegetables in 2 tablespoons bacon grease for 5 minutes.
Add rice, crumbled bacon and eggs.
Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Warm all. Serve with Soy Chicken:

title: kolaches
directions: Soak yeast.
Mix lukewarm milk, sugar and salt; stir until dissolved.
Add melted shortening.
Add 2 cups flour (sifted) and beat.
Add the beaten eggs and yeast; blend well.
Add rest of flour; blend well.
Cover.
Let rise.
Punch down; let rise again.

title: hot 'n tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in small saucepan.
Simmer 20 minutes. Brush sauce on spareribs, chicken or hamburgers during baking, broiling or grilling.

title: chili
directions: Heat fat in a large boiler and cook meat until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cook slowly until done; about 1 1/2 to to hours.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cocoa, soda and baking powder.
Add zucchini when all other ingredients are mixed well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in greased loaf pans.

title: fat man salad
directions: Drain
pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Mix in pecans and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix marshmallows in last.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, jelly and eggs.
Dissolve soda in milk and add to mixture.
Sift half the flour and all of the spices, then add to butter mixture.
Use remaining flour to dredge all of the fruit and nuts.
Then add to butter mixture.
Stir well and drop small spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
(Batter will appear dry.)
Cook at 300°
about 15 minutes.
Cookies ripen with age.

title: aunt nita's sour cream softies
directions: Combine egg, sugar, sour cream and oleo in bowl.
Sift dry ingredients together and combine everything, then add chocolate chips.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes or until light golden brown on edges.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: scrambled deluxe
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
Combine egg, peppers and Tabasco.
