Mix with cheese and sausage mixture.
Scramble to desired consistency.

title: amaretti
directions: Lightly grease 3 cookie sheets.
Process almonds and sugar in food processor or blender, until finely ground.
Beat egg whites in a large bowl with electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
Beat in extract.
Gently stir in almond mixture.
Result will be a thick, sticky paste.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 1 1/2
inches apart on prepared cookie sheets.
Dust top with confectioners sugar stirred through a sieve.
Let stand 2 hours at room temperature, so cookies retain shape and tops dry.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion and celery in bacon drippings for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Put into casserole and bake at 350° for one hour. Sprinkle noodles on top after baking and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and sour cream. Put vegetables and bacon in large bowl. Pour sauce over vegetables. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in shortening.
Add beef and brown until crumbly, but not hard.
Pour off drippings.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, cayenne pepper, oregano and bay leaf. Cover and cook slowly 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.

title: fruit crush
directions: Mix water and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit juices and mashed bananas.
Pour into four ice trays and freeze until firm.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar, peanuts, white Karo and salt together
and microwave 4 minutes.
Stir and microwave 3 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Add soda.
Stir fast and pour immediately on greased cookie sheet.
Cool and crack.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour; mix well.
Add fruits and nuts along with whiskey.
Bake in a large Bundt pan at 200° for 4 hours.

title: rice and green chiles
directions: Blend sour cream and milk together in a bowl.
Add rice and mix.
Add chiles, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and white Karo syrup.
Add the peanut butter.
Add the whole corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Very quick to make and very yummy.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Blend together.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: glazed yeast doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine boiling water, shortening and sugar in large bowl; stir in 1 cup milk.
Add eggs and yeast; mix well.
Add flour; mix well until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; cover.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
This is a real stiff batter.
You have to use your fingers to press it in the pan.
Beat eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Mix well; pour over cake.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry christmas salad
directions: Drain cranberries and crush, a few at a time in blender or food processor.
Pour sugar over berries and let sit.
Mix strawberry jello with boiling water.
Do not add cold water.
Mix in berries and sugar.
Pour in mold and refrigerate until set.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Arrange spears in large buttered baking dish or casserole.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until nicely browned. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese straw biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Do not grease pan.

title: potato and kale soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat margarine over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic and saute for about 5 minutes, or until softened. Add stock, potatoes and red pepper flakes and simmer, covered, for about 20 minutes, or until the potatoes are tender.
Transfer half the potatoes and 1 cup cooking liquid to a blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Meanwhile, steam kale for 5 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir it into the soup.
Heat through and season with salt and pepper.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple cherry crunch
directions: Grease baking dish with small amount of butter.
Pour crushed pineapple and cherry pie filling, including juices, into buttered dish. Pour cake mix over fruit and place butter pats on top of the mix.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: board meeting fruit dip
directions: Slice apples into wedges, leaving skin on for color.
Soak in orange juice for at least 1 hour.
Cream together the cream cheese, marshmallow cream and lemon juice.
Arrange drained apples around flat serving dish; place dip (in bowl) in the center.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then nuts.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: karen sherman's open-faced quesadillas
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan for this recipe.
Add the ingredients in layers, using half the ingredients in each layer.

title: supreme mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes according to the directions on package.
Place potatoes in an electric mixer bowl.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Blend; add garlic powder and onion salt. Blend until smooth.
Place mix in a greased 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
You can freeze this and bake later.

title: crispy cornflake cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caddy cooler
directions: Mix juices, strawberries and ice in blender for 15 seconds. Makes 1 serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In frying pan cook hamburger, onion and green pepper with lid on until onion and pepper are tender.
Add tomato soup, catsup and salt and pepper to hamburger.
Cook until all is hot and stir in cooked macaroni.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with sliced cheese.
Cover and bake on 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour milk doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar and beat smooth.
Stir in melted shortening
and
vanilla.
Add,
alternating
milk, flour, baking powder, soda
and salt, mixing to a smooth, soft dough. Turn out on a
floured surface; knead, pat and roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with
floured
cutter.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, sausage, bread crumbs, parsley, garlic, green onion, egg, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Form into 1 inch balls.
Arrange in a ring on microwave roasting rack.
Cook on 80 for 5-6 minutes.
Turn meatballs over; cook on 80 for 3-4 minutes.
Place meatballs on serving platter.
Cover with aluminum foil; set aside.
Pour drippings into 2 c. glass measure.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook on HI for 1 1/2 minutes or until hot.
Pour over meatballs.
Serve with garlic bread and your favorite pasta.
Makes 12 meatballs.
Total cooking time:

title: pumpkin tea ring
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Store in refrigerator.
Lasts a long time.

title: lee's spaghetti sauce(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker; cover and cook on low 3 to 4 hours.

title: garden chowder
directions: In 5 quart Dutch oven over medium heat saute bacon for 3 minutes or until crisp.
With slotted spoon, remove bacon and set aside.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onion and green pepper; saute 3 minutes longer.
Stir in potato soup, the broth, cream and milk; bring to boiling.
Add broccoli, cauliflower and corn.
Simmer covered 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and the bacon.

title: cheese ball
directions: After cheese is room temperature, grate and mix well with sauces.
Finely chop 1/2 cup pecans and roll cheese ball in pecans and chill.

title: smothered hamburger patties
directions: Shape meat patties and fry until browned.
Pour off excessive grease and return meat to pan.
Put 1 slice of onion and 1 slice of green pepper on each patty.
Pour tomatoes over them and simmer for 35 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: easy no cook relish
directions: Combine apples, onions, celery and pickles.
Chop in food processor, using metal blade.
Add vinegar, sugar and mustard to ground mixture.
Mix well.
Cover container and store in the refrigerator.
Yields about 4 cups.
Can be stored in refrigerator up to 10 days.

title: tuscan rice
directions: Cook the rice in plenty of boiling salted water until al dente; drain.

title: yeast rolls(yields 48 dinner rolls)
directions: Dissolve the sugar, Crisco, salt and water with the 1 cup of boiling water.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Pour beaten eggs into the first mixture when mixture has cooled.
Add yeast and water mixture to the mixture when yeast has dissolved and mixture is cool.
Stir in 2 cups of flour at a time into the liquid mixture until all 6 cups have been added.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Let rise 3 times and stir to release air each time it rises.
Do not knead.

title: homemade pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add oil, sugar and salt; mix well. Add flour and mix.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.

title: fresh summer salsa
directions: Cook bacon in a large Dutch oven until crisp; remove bacon, reserve 2 tablespoons of drippings in Dutch oven.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion in reserved drippings until tender. Stir in tomatoes and simmer 15 minutes.
Add next 5 ingredients. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onion.
Add flour.
Cook broccoli until done (package directions); drain.
Add to chicken broth; add onion mixture.
Bring to boil, stirring to keep from sticking.
Just before serving, add milk.
Do not boil after adding milk.

title: longhorn cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Cool, then fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until firm in 9 x 13-inch flat dish.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Put a layer of chocolate cake pieces, drizzled with Kahlua in a bowl.
Add dollops of pudding, then dollops of whipped cream and repeat steps, ending with whipped cream.
Crumble candy on top and refrigerate.
Can be made a day or 2 in advance.

title: cinnamon dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together until creamy and smooth.
Dip apples (or any fruit) in it.
Makes 1 cup.

title: swiss party chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put chicken in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Pour in mushrooms.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: seven-up poke and pour cake
directions: Put mixture in 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake according to directions on cake mix box.
Poke holes in cake.
Pour Jell-O over cake.
Refrigerate for 3 or 4 hours.
Then spread Cool Whip topping on cake and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; set aside.

title: hamburger tater tots casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain, then season. Lay in the bottom of an 8 1/2 x 11-inch dish. Next, layer vegetables or you can mix with hamburger. Pour 1/2 of soup in bottom if you mix vegetables and hamburger; mix soup also. Layer your Tater Tots on top of mixture and pop in the oven for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: "fireman's" barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender or with hand mixer. Store in refrigerator.
Great for nuggets!

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well. Spread into a 9-inch pie plate. Spread pizza sauce on top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, green onion and bell pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer. Serve with crackers.

title: bean salad
directions: Dissolve in a pan and let come to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Keeps well.

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Mix all well with mixer.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: will's chili burro's(enchilada style)
directions: Place 3 tablespoons of chili on tortilla, roll tortilla while folding in ends. Pour enchilada sauce over tortillas.
Grate cheese over burros and warm in microwave until cheese is melted on top.

title: brazzole
directions: Flank or thin round steak.
Make each piece separately. Sprinkle to taste with salt, garlic (powder or minced), parsley and grated Romano cheese.
Roll the steak and keep in place with string or toothpicks.
Cook or fry until brown.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.

title: chocolate shortcake
directions: Sift
flour, sugar and salt together; set aside.
Place butter, Crisco, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil
and
pour over flour and sugar.
Stir well and add the buttermilk, vanilla, soda and eggs.
Beat well and pour into a 16 x
11-inch	pan.
Bake at 350° until done.	(See "Chocolate Icing" recipe in this same section to ice this cake.)

title: egg nog
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until whites begin to stiffen.
In another large bowl, beat the yolks until they drop from the spoon in a heavy ribbon.
Beat the whites into the yolks until thoroughly blended. In a large bowl, whip the cream until it begins to hold its shape. Beat the egg gradually into the cream.
Stir in milk.
Pour mixture into the punch bowl.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.

title: noodle delight(quick, easy and yummy)
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Pour in cans of cream of chicken soup.
Add milk, salt and pepper; stir.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. (Meat lovers add extra boiled chicken.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, salt and vanilla.
Place pecans in pastry shell, then add mixture on top of pecans.
Bake at 350° until filling is firm and pecans rise to top and forms a custard layer.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses together.
Add few drops of maraschino cherry juice.
Add a few drops of Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Chill.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill well.

title: caramel-chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1/2 of the can of Pet milk.
The mixture will be coarse.
Pat half of it in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 (7-ounce) plastic cups.

title: sour cream blueberry cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add gradually to egg mixture, alternating with sour cream, ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla and cardamon.
Fold in 1 cup blueberries.
Pour half the batter into well-greased and floured pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch or fluted Bundt pan.
Cover with remaining blueberries.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes (15 for Bundt pan).
Remove to rack to finish cooling (remove Bundt cake from pan).
Serve with whipped topping.

title: quick and easy fluff
directions: Mix condensed milk, pie filling and drained pineapple.
Add Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut pie
directions: Whip cheese till soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold topping into mixture.
Pour into pie shell, sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Freeze until firm and serve.
Can be refrozen if not used.
Wrap in sealing paper after pie is frozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well the eggs, sugar and oil.
Gradually add flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add grated carrots and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 layer pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: oven french fries
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Slice each half into lengthwise wedges with some peel on each wedge.
Soak in cold ice water for 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 450°.
Spray baking sheet with vegetable oil, spray liberally.
Drain and dry potatoes.
Place in plastic bag with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Close tightly and shake to coat.
Arrange in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally for about 20 minutes, until golden and crisp.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.

title: home made cherry pie
directions: Rinse and drain cherries. Place in a large mixing bowl. Pour sugar over cherries. and then pour flour over the cherries. Add almond extract, lemon juice and condensed milk. Beat together and let stand for a few minutes. Prepare the pastry shell, either home made or refrigerator. Roll out the pastry shell and place in a pie pan. Add the filling. Take the top pastry and cut it into 1 inch strips. Weave to cover pie. Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes, then hake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer boiled chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Next, layer eggs (sliced) over chicken.
Mix vegetables, soup and broth together.
Pour over chicken and eggs.
Mix oleo, flour and milk together.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake in oven at 350° until brown crust forms on top, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool and peel potatoes.
Mash potatoes coarsely.
Add all ingredients and stir vigorously.
Serve cold. Top with chopped eggs.

title: black bean-tortilla casserole
directions: In a large skillet combine first 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in beans*.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread 1/3 of the bean mixture over bottom. Top with corn tortillas, overlapping as necessary, and Monterey Jack cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with bean mixture.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until heated through.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; add to butter mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
Serve hot.
Makes 16 four-ounce servings.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Grate carrots and cabbage.
Dice other ingredients and mix well.

title: easy caesar salad and dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except lettuce; set aside.

title: aunt mema's creamy green enchiladas
directions: Combine beef and salt; brown in skillet.
Drain.
Stir in cheese and onion; set aside.
Combine soup, milk and cheese spread in a medium saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Add onion dip mix and chilies; set aside.
Dip tortillas in hot oil to soften, about 1 second; drain.
Spread each tortilla with meat mixture.
Roll tightly and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Pour cheese sauce over tortillas.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
I sometimes fix this as a casserole to save time, layering the tortillas and meat instead of rolling them individually.
Still very good.

title: sarah's chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, grapes and celery in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix other ingredients.
Pour mixture over the chicken, grapes and celery.
Let rest for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Reserve 1/2 can Chinese noodles.
Mix remaining ingredients together in casserole.
Top with reserved noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 cobbler
directions: Take fruit and place in bottom of pan; spread evenly.
In a mixing bowl, mix milk, flour and sugar; mix well.
Pour over fruit as evenly as possible.
Bake until crust turns brown, about 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: clara's party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together;
let set until all soaked through.
Store in large container.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, then fold lime sherbet in.
Can substitute orange or pineapple for limeade and sherbet.

title: sauce or dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Place in crock-pot.
Cook 1/2 hour to 1 hour.
Serve with chips.

title: baked alaska
directions: Beat egg whites until they become stiff. Add sugar, beating well.
Cut cake and ice cream in thick slices.
Stack alternately on pan.
Cover well with thick meringue, making sure to cover the sides well.
Bake at 400°.
This is a good dish to fix for your grandchildren.

title: french dressing(1960's recipe, homemade)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let set 1/2 hour in refrigerator.

title: grandmom's bread
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
After sifting flour, add yeast and salt.
Heat water and milk to lukewarm, do not boil.
Add oleo and sugar to warmed liquid.
Add 1/2 of dry ingredients to liquids. Mix well and then add remainder of dry ingredients.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes on floured surface.
Place in greased/buttered bowl and cover with damp cloth (turn dough once in bowl so all sides are greased).
Put in warm (not hot) area.
Raise 1 hour or until double in size.
Knead and shape into loaves or rolls, let rise until double in size.
Makes 2 loaves or approximately 1 dozen cupcake sized rolls.
Bake:
Loaves 35 to 40 minutes, rolls 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until done. Drain off water. Put rice in baking dish. Add broccoli, Cheez Whiz and soup and mix well. Add 1 can of water before you mix. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pickled corn
directions: Before cutting corn off the cob, parboil long enough to set the milk in the kernels.
Cut the corn off the cob, but do not scrape the cob.
Pack cut corn into quart jars.
Place 2 heaping tablespoons of coarse pickling salt in each jar; fill with water. Seal tight and store in a cool place.
To serve, rinse before cooking.

title: igloo chilli
directions: Cook beef and onions until done; drain.
Add tomato sauce, brown sugar and chilli powder; mix together and simmer on low heat about 30 minutes.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Mix with all other ingredients and heat in 350° oven, uncovered, until bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes or heat in crock-pot longer.
Serves 10.

title: lettuce and pea salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Break lettuce into bite-sized pieces in a large flat serving dish.
Thaw the peas and sprinkle them over the lettuce as soon as they are thawed enough to do so.
Mix the onion, celery, green pepper, mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour over the lettuce and peas.
Sprinkle cheese over this, followed by the bacon pieces.
Chill overnight.

title: albondigas(meatballs - spain)
directions: Combine meat, salt, nutmeg and parsley.
Squeeze water from bread, add bread and egg to meat mixture and work to a paste. Form into small balls and saute in olive oil.
Serve hot this way or keep warm in sauce made of equal parts of sherry and gelatined beef bouillon.

title: creamy italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine and stir mayonnaise, wine vinegar, garlic, basil, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Stir in pasta and remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve at favorite barbecue.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together; press into a greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and take from pan.

title: cold soap
directions: Mix ammonia in 1/2 cup water, then pour into the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour in large pan until set.
Cut into bars.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly brown all spareribs.
Combine all remaining ingredients to make a sauce.
Place ribs in baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 3 hours at 350°.
Baste often.

title: barbecue meatballs in crock-pot
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Shape balls 1-inch in diameter. Place on cookie sheet and brown in 350° oven, but don't overcook. When done, place in a slow cooker. Add sauce to cooker and cook on high until it begins to bubble, then cook on low for about 4 hours.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Saute onions in small amount of butter.
In medium saucepan mix together and warm onions, broth, soups and Ro-Tel.
In 9 x 11-inch casserole dish layer 1/2 of chicken, 1/2 of soup mixture, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of Doritos.
Then layer the other 1/2 in the same order.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes, just long enough to heat everything thoroughly and make cheese melt.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Place potatoes in a large pot and allow to boil until tender. Dice the onion and place in a large frying pan with 1/2 teaspoon of butter; stir-fry until brown.
Add the ground beef, salt and pepper to taste until tender and brown.
Do not drain.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth and blend in sugar.
Next comes sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well and pour into crust.
Chill at least 6 hours and spoon on cherries.

title: saucy green beans
directions: Saute celery in melted butter until tender.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Gradually blend in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Gently stir in drained green beans and pimientos.
Heat thoroughly over low heat.

title: polka dot cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt over low heat butter and semi-sweet chocolate chips, stirring constantly.
Allow to cool. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir egg mixture into melted chocolate until smooth, combine with flour.
Stir in white chocolate chips and nuts.
Chill until stiff.
Drop by well-rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Make paste of cocoa and vinegar, then add to mixture. Sift flour and salt together and add to mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla and food coloring. Bake at 325° to 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned egg pie
directions: Dissolve butter in scalded milk.
Beat eggs. Add sugar, salt and scalded milk or butter.
Add vanilla. Mix well and pour into large pie crust, uncooked. Garnish with nutmeg. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until shell baked.

title: baked rice custard
directions: In 1 1/4 cups water, cook rice.
Bring rice to a boil; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until all moisture is absorbed. Cool slightly.
Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt and milk.
Mix (low speed) only until mixed.
Add rice, raisins, milk, butter and vanilla to egg mixture.
Blend well.
Put into shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg if desired.
Place in water bath and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean. Serve with a garnish of sweetened whipped cream.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onion very thin.
Layer in large baking dish.
Dot with margarine.
Mix milk and flour; pour over potatoes and onion.
Take a spoon and move potatoes around so as to cover with milk.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: jello salad
directions: Cut and drain fruit.
Mix dry Jell-O into cottage cheese.
Mix fruit and cottage cheese and add Cool Whip; chill.
Good.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of the cocoa and coloring.
Sift the dry ingredients; add to the creamed mixture and cocoa; mix alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, soda and vinegar last.
Pour into two greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn-rice casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients except paprika.
Pour into a buttered shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: needhams
directions: Boil and mash potato.
Let cool.
(Too much potato makes mixture wet.)
Mix in confectioners sugar, vanilla and coconut. Line 8-inch square pan with plastic wrap.
Spread coconut mixture evenly over plastic.
Cover with 2 squares melted chocolate.
Cool about 30 minutes, until chocolate is set.
(Okay to cool in refrigerator.
Will take longer on countertop.)
Grasp plastic securely and flip chocolate covered coconut mix onto flat surface. Return mix to pan, chocolate side down.
Peel plastic off.
Cover with other 2 melted chocolate squares.
Let cool.
As soon as chocolate sets, cut into squares.
Refrigerate.

title: reduced fat chili verdi
directions: To Cook Roast:
Bake at 350°, covered, with 2 cups of water for 4 hours. Add more water if it gets too dry.

title: pear bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine oil, egg, sugar, pears, and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased 8-1/2 X 4-1/2 X 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until bread test done. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: poulet de normandic
directions: Mix together stuffing mix, margarine and water.
Place one-half of mixture in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over bread mixture in baking dish and top with remaining half of bread mixture.
Blend eggs and 1/2 cup milk and pour over top. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking.

title: oven spicy carrots
directions: Combine ingredients in baking dish and cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: honey biscuits for two
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Cut in the butter until crumbly.
Stir in honey and milk just until moistened.
Place on floured surface; with floured hands, knead gently 8 to 10 times. Roll to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 biscuits.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cool.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add salt, pepper and mustard.
Mix in bread cubes.
Add cheese and sausage; stir.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend and pour over cake.

title: poppy seed muffins(makes 32 to 40 mini muffins or 12 regular muffins)
directions: Mix and blend all ingredients together.
Pour into muffin pans lined with appropriate size papers or grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes for mini size or a bit longer for larger muffins.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Drain oil.
Add garlic powder, salt, soup mix, puree, pepper and oregano.
Cook until thick (15 to 20 minutes).

title: apple-tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In saucepan melt margarine over low heat.
Blend in flour and salt. Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in tuna, apple and macaroni; turn into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs and melted margarine.
Sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender, 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and Pet milk.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes, stir.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes, stir. Microwave on High for 3 minutes, stir and add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Let cool for 30 to 35 minutes in buttered pan.

title: mile high fudge brownie pie
directions: Microwave chocolate and butter on High 2 minutes or until butter is melted. Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Add sugar; stir until well blended. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Stir in flour. Spread into greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool completely on wire rack. Scoop out center of brownie, leaving 1/2-inch thick rim around edge and thin layer of brownie on bottom. Reserve brownie pieces.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook salt pork, covered, over medium heat until fat is rendered (6 minutes).
Add onion.
Cook until brown, stirring often.
Stir in spinach until well blended.
Keep warm.
Heat butter until melted; add flour.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring slowly.
Add milk and cream slowly.
Heat to a boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add seasoning and spinach.
Stir well.
Heat through. Can make the day before covered airtight.
Gently reheat on stove top or microwave.

title: frosty pineapple pie
directions: Bring to boil the pineapple.
Stir in the lemon jello until well dissolved.
Mix in sugar.
Cool until almost stiff.
Whip evaporated milk along with the lemon juice until stiff.
Pour on top of gelatin mixture and beat slowly on low speed until well blended.
Put into crust and chill for at least 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: fresh cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Combine juice and rind with egg. Pour into dry ingredients.
Mix just enough to dampen.
Carefully fold in nuts and chopped cranberries.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Spread corners slightly higher than centers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until crust is golden brown.

title: special chicken
directions: Stir together dressing, jam and soup.
Pour over chicken breasts and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with rice, if desired.

title: chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 8 x 2 1/2-inch diameter ring mold with unflavored cooking spray.
Set aside.
Combine melted butter and sugar until they just come together.
Scrape down side of bowl.
Add melted chocolate; mix until combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, until combined.
Sift flour, cocoa powder and salt together.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients all at once and combine by using an electric mixer.
Start on low speed and increase to medium.

title: gingersnaps
directions: In big bowl, mix half of the flour, brown sugar, shortening, molasses, egg, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat with electric mixer on medium to high speed until mixed well.
Beat in rest of flour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Add rice.
Pour boiling water over.
Add meat. Mix soups and milk.
Add to the other mixture.
Bake in oblong pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli and onion in small pieces.
Break up fried bacon and mix in raisins.
Mix Miracle Whip and vinegar; toss with all ingredients.
Let set 1 hour before serving.

title: pork loin and sauce
directions: The original recipe said to marinate the pork loin in this sauce.
I do this and also bake the loin in the sauce.
Bake in a 325° oven, covered, until the meat is no longer pink inside. Uncover the last 30 minutes of baking time.
Thicken the sauce in the pan with a little flour and water and dribble a little of this over slices of the roast pork.

title: trail food
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom and sides of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool slightly.
Add honey and vanilla.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in ingredients from saucepan. Mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Press into pan.
Bake 20 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars. Makes about 24 bars.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon and break into pieces.
Cut up both lettuce and cauliflower and put in bowl.
Add bacon and cheese; toss.
Ten minutes before serving, mix Miracle Whip and sugar.
Pour over salad.
Toss again and serve.

title: saucy fruit glaze(glaze for ham)
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Spoon over ham surface during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Makes enough glaze for a 4 pound half ham.
Double recipe for whole ham.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 3/4 cup for topping.

title: pear  mincemeat
directions: Quarter and core all fruits. Do not peel.
Run all through food chopper with coarse blade.
Mix all together. Cook slowly, stirring often, about 2 hours or until thick as desired.
Seal in jars.
(Very good for pies and cookies.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Cut into chunks (about 2 cups) and put into baking dish.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and cream of chicken soup, salt and pepper and pour over chicken.
Melt butter and mix with crumbled crackers.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bourbon casserole
directions: Saute meat and vegetables.
Add soup, cooked noodles and remaining ingredients.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Form meat into patties, then fry until done.
Remove from pan and pour off grease.
Mix soup, water, salt and pepper in the pan. Heat until boiling and add patties.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: low-fat lemon creme pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg whites with Eagle Brand low-fat, lemon juice and food coloring if desired.
Pour into prepared pastry shell; bake 30 minutes.
Cool. Chill.
Spread with topping.
Attractive if garnished with lemon slices.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dinner biscuits
directions: Use two refrigerator biscuits for each bunny.
Cut one biscuit in half for the ears.
Press into the second biscuit.
Decorate with raisin eyes and cherry nose.

title: butterscotch date cream pie
directions: In double boiler, heat the milk with butter.
Beat egg yolks, then stir in combined sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to heated milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thick and smooth. Add dates and vanilla.
Refrigerate until cold.
Turn into baked pie shell and refrigerate.
Just before serving garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: spanish rice enchiladas
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain. Set aside 1 tablespoon taco seasoning. Add remaining seasoning to beef. Stir in 3/4 cup water. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven at 450°.
Mix all ingredients.
In large iron skillet pour in enough oil to cover bottom of skillet.
Pour in all of cornbread mix.
Bake at 450° until golden brown or about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grill cheese sandwich
directions: Butter
the bread
on
both
sides.
Place
the
cheese between the sliced bread
and
cook in an iron skillet or on a grill until cheese
is melted, turning the bread frequently so as not to burn the bread.
Serves 1 or 2.

title: chicken stuff-a-roni
directions: Combine milk and mushroom soup; set aside.
Boil 2 quarts water.
Add Stuff-A-Roni and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Boil for 8 minutes.
Rinse under warm water.
Mix Cheddar cheese, chicken, broccoli, bread and egg.
In an 11 x 7-inch baking dish, pour 1 cup soup.
Stuff the Stuff-A-Roni with chicken mixture; place, one deep, in baking dish.
Pour remaining soup over.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Add remaining Mozzarella.
Bake for 5 minutes. Serve.

title: cocoa raisin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 350° oven until done. Makes 2 layers.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Remove the stems from the strawberries, wash and cut into small pieces.
Combine with the Grand Marnier and sugar and let stand for 15 to 20 minutes.
Preheat the oven to 425° to 450°. Brush cups of muffin pans with melted butter.

title: curried chicken
directions: Sprinkle
salt,
pepper
and curry powder over chicken. Saute in
margarine
over
medium
heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Can be served as an appetizer on toothpicks or as an entree over rice.

title: blender pie
directions: In blender, blend at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: huguenot torte(from charleston, south carolina)
directions: Beat egg until lemon colored and fluffy. Gradually add sugar. Beat until smooth. Set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add to egg and sugar mixture. Add nuts, apple and vanilla. Generously butter an 8 x 8-inch pan or pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: adobo
directions: Place chicken in greased pan.
Put slice of Swiss cheese on each chicken breast.

title: baked salmon with tomatoes, spinach & mushrooms
directions: Place salmon fillets, skin sides down, in 13 x 9 inch baking dish sprayed with non stick cooking spray. Mix remaining ingredients until well blended; spoon over salmon. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until salmon flakes easily when tested with fork. This has 5 grams carbohydrate.

title: pepper relish
directions: Use about 3 dozen medium peppers; if red peppers are not available, use green peppers.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch quiche dish or deep dish pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Crisply fry and crumble bacon. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
No adjustments are necessary for high altitude (3,500 to 6,500 feet).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tuna unique
directions: Boil macaroni, drain.
Add butter, cheese and milk.
Drain tuna and add to mixture.
Serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in molasses, sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm; measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle or crumble in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture.
Add 1 cup white flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough of each kind of remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn on floured board and knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl to rise until double in bulk or 40 minutes.
Punch down; shape into rolls and let rise until double for 30 minutes.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple isle dessert
directions: Take 1/2 of vanilla wafers and press into the bottom of well-buttered casserole dish, then blend well the eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Pour on top of crumbs as second layer, then for third layer, put on crushed pineapple.
As fourth layer, spread on whip cream; fifth layer, sprinkle on the nuts, then sprinkle on remainder of vanilla wafers.
Chill in refrigerator 3 or 4 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: double chocolate trifle
directions: In quart bowl, whisk pudding mix into milk using 10-inch whisk until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in whipped topping using rubber scraper.
Crumble 1/3 brownies into bottom of Chillzanne bowl.
Top with 1/3 of pudding
mixture, pressing lightly.
Top with 1/3 toffee.
Repeat last step 2 more times. Chill 30 minutes before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: meringue surprises(lo-fat cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 375° for 15 minutes.
Beat egg whites until a little foamy.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat well.
Gradually add in sugar.
Beat well.
Add food coloring, as desired.
Fold in one package mint chocolate chips.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Turn off the oven just before putting cookies in.
Leave in cooled oven overnight or at least 5 to 8 hours.
(Don't peek!)
Makes 2 dozen.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread dinner rolls on pizza pan.
Mix all ingredients except 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Add cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter.
Beat in sugar and vanilla. Add milk until frosting reaches desired consistency.
Yields approximately 4 cups.

title: thirty-day slaw
directions: Grate (fine) the cabbage and onion.
Bring other ingredients to a boil.
Pour over raw cabbage and onion.
(Use glass bowl, not plastic.)
Cover and refrigerate.
Keeps 30 days.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes. Gradually beat in sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.

Sift together dry ingredients and fold into egg mixture. Spread in greased and floured jelly roll pan. Batter will be thin. Top with 1 cup chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes. Turn onto clean dish towel sprinkled with powdered sugar. Roll cake and towel together while still hot.

title: fresh homemade apple pie
directions: Place apples, flour, sugar and cinnamon in bowl and mix together to coat apples. Put in pie shell and place cut up butter over apple mixture.Place another pie shell over first one and poke holes in top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Bring milk and margarine to boil over medium heat.
Add flour, all at once, and stir constantly until mixture forms a ball and leaves the sides of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased foil lined cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until puffs are golden brown.

title: corned beef and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix soup and milk.
Add onion flakes.
Heat.
Add cheese.
Cook until melted.
Add corned beef and macaroni.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until well browned.

title: crabbies
directions: Sort through crabmeat and remove any membranes.
Soften margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on half of English muffin.
Cut into quarters.
Broil until slightly brown. Covers about 12 muffin halves.
Serve warm.

title: meat filled tacos
directions: Warm shells in oven at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Stir in seasoning mix and water.
Heat to boiling on low heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until liquid is reduced.

title: yamber apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
In medium bowl combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Using pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 3/4 cup pastry mixture and set aside.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops.
Place in a Pyrex dish.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Pour mixture over chops.
Cover and cook for 2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: lazy man's enchiladas
directions: Brown desired amount of ground beef and onions; drain. Dip tortilla shells in sauce and layer bottom of casserole dish. Put a little sauce over layer. Spread ground beef. Sprinkle lots of cheese. Dip more shells in sauce for another layer. Repeat if necessary. Spread remaining sauce on top layer of shells. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and heat until melted.

title: creamy veggie spread
directions: In bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Blend in curry powder, and then cheese.
Put in serving bowl.
Chill for 30 minutes so flavors blend.
Serve with veggies, breads or as a sandwich filler alone or with lunch meats.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix corn meal and salt; combine with cold milk and stir until smooth.
Add to hot milk and cook until thickened (about 5 minutes, stirring constantly).

Beat eggs; add small amount of cooked mixture; blend, then add remainder of cooked mixture and butter. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil. Blend well.
Stir in zucchini.

title: date balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir constantly.
Add vanilla and mix.
Then add Rice Krispies cereal and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
When cool enough to handle, form into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: beefy chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Shred dried beef into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken over beef.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 2 hours.

title: vermont pork chops
directions: Secure 1 large elephant.
Kill, clean and cut into small cubes.
This will take about 2 months.
Put into large kettle and simmer over kerosene at 465° for 14 weeks.
Make gravy to cover. This will feed 3,685 people.
If more meat is needed, add 2 rabbits, but use only if necessary, as very few people care for hare in their stew!

title: spinach balls(appetizer)
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix all ingredients together. Shape into bite size balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Can be frozen before baking.
Yields 60 to 70 balls.

title: out of this world fruit salad
directions: Mix instant pudding with juices and pour over mixed fruit. Chill.

title: party punch
directions: Thaw frozen juices.
Mix all ingredients together and float cherries and orange slices on top.

title: creamed vegetables
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir vegetables into sauce; heat through.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Heat oil; add onions and cook until soft.
Add water and bouillon cubes; boil until dissolved.
Add noodles and salt; cook uncovered three minutes.
Add garlic and broccoli; cook four minutes.
Add milk and cheese, dash of pepper; cook on very low heat and stir until cheese is melted.

title: date nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add egg yolks one at a time, then add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Then sift over nuts and dates.
Mix this to cream mixture.
Last, add 4 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: chipped beef and cream cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chipped beef, and shape into balls.
Spread a layer of chipped beef on cookie sheet and place in 350° oven until dry and crisp (about 15 minutes).
Cool and crumble.
Roll cream cheese balls in crumbled beef.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, salt and lemon juice. Beat well. Sift flour and baking soda together and add gradually to first mixture. Batter is quite stiff before apples and pecans are added. Add apples and pecans. Blend well. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan in a preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done. Cool on a wire rack.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice and add cold water to measure 1 cup.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in cold water. Refrigerate until slightly thick.
Stir in whipped topping, pineapple, oranges and marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Rinse and cut tops off bell peppers for stuffing.
In mixing bowl, mix all ingredients except peppers.
Sprinkle salt and black pepper generously, because a lot of the flavor boils out during cooking.
Stuff this mixture into peppers.
Place peppers upright in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour about 1 inch of water into bottom of pan without getting water in peppers.
Bake in oven at 375°, covered tightly, for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: old time mincemeat pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat.
Cook 1 hour.
Add meat. Cook 15 minutes.
Spoon into bottom pie shell.
Top with second crust.
Seal edges. Cut steam vents.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce to 350° and bake 50 minutes.
Cover edges with foil if crust browns too quickly.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream. Dee-lish!

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and blend well.
Pour into a greased baking pan and top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cinnamon ornaments(not to eat-for christmas decoration)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, blending well.
Stir in applesauce.
Mix well.
(Mixture will be stiff.)
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: electric skillet pork chop casserole
directions: Heat oil in electric skillet, place pork chops in skillet and brown on one side; turn heat to 300° and add sliced potatoes, can of tomatoes, can of green beans and dill weed.
Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Good.

title: herbed stuffed eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Scoop out yolks in a large bowl.
Set egg white halves aside.
Mash yolks; blend in cheese spread and mayonnaise, scallions, pimientos and mustard until smooth.
Spoon or pipe yolk mixture into egg white halves.
Garnish with sliced scallions and serve.

title: evelyn's sweet potato pie
directions: Mash sweet potatoes, add melted butter, sugar, egg yolks, salt, flavorings, milk and mix.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° for 25 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine butter or oleo, sugar and salt in mixer.
Mix well and add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Add scalded milk slowly and then vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for approximately 25 minutes.
Top will be browning and firm, but shimmering.

title: roll-em-ups
directions: Pound steak on both sides.
Cut into 3-inch strips.
Place a strip of bacon and a slice of onion on each strip.
Fold over and tie with thin string.
Heat oil or shortening in skillet over medium heat.
Flour meat and brown in skillet.
Add a little water and simmer for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple roll cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Combine flour, powder and salt.
Mix alternately with enough milk to moisten (like biscuit dough).
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with raisins, thin sliced apples and nuts.
Sprinkle on some sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
Roll like jelly roll.
Use waxed paper to help roll.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Ice with thin icing when cold.

title: coffee glaze
directions: In small saucepan, heat milk, butter or margarine and coffee until butter or margarine has melted. Add to confectioners sugar. Blend until smooth. This is great on spice cake.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in 1/2 of chocolate chips.
Spread evenly into well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 of chocolate chips; wait 5 minutes, then spread.

title: sausage and egg puff
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage, breaking up any large lumps. Drain. In a 2-quart casserole, layer sausage, bread and cheese. In a bowl, beat eggs with remaining ingredients. Pour over layers in casserole. Cover and refrigerate 12 hours or overnight. Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: "dirt"
directions: Mix cream, margarine and powdered sugar together, then fold in Cool Whip.
In another large bowl, mix the pudding, milk and vanilla and then combine the ingredients of both bowls.
Crush Oreos in food processor until they get to the consistency of "dirt."
Layer Oreos and pudding mixture in a new flowerpot, ending with a layer of Oreos.
Garnish with artificial flowers, gummi worms, etc.
Serve with a new garden spade.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat well the oil and eggs, then add remaining cake ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Excellent, moist cake.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and spices to a boil.
Pour over onions and zucchini and let stand one hour.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Pack in sterile hot jars.
Adjust lids and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Remove jars and let stand until cool before storing.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Make white sauce with butter, flour, salt, pepper and liquid. Cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add beaten eggs, then corn. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350°.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch and sugar in water.
Cook until thick. Stir in the peach jello; cool and pour over sliced peaches put in baked pie shell.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding mix over pineapple in a medium serving bowl. Mix.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: cheese ball(2 large or 4 small)
directions: I use Oscar and mince very fine the bell pepper, celery and nuts.
Grate cheese and mix by hand with cream cheese.
Add pineapple, pepper, garlic, salt and nuts.
Roll into ball or shape in a mold.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, roll in chopped nuts completely.
Serve with crackers.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup of soup and remaining ingredients. Shape into 6 patties.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done, breaking into bits as you cook it. Drain and set aside.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Into a greased baking dish, layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over these ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
Great for overnight guest or Christmas morning.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash the beans.
Mix the sugar, beans, coconut, margarine, eggs and vanilla together.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.
Let cool, then cut.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn and put in oven.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cup brownies
directions: Make brownie mix as directed on box.
Put 2 Tbsp. of mix in foil cup.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Drop a peanut butter cup into the center of each brownie and bake for another 6 minutes.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream and milk together well. Add chopped green pepper, onion and chipped beef. Blend all ingredients with mixer.
Pour mixture into ovenproof bowl.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve hot with cut vegetables or crackers to dip.

title: tofu enchiladas
directions: Mix tofu and remaining ingredients.
Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Cover bottom of pan with sauce.
Prepare tortillas by toasting lightly in toaster oven until soft.
Spread each tortilla with a little sauce and a portion of the tofu mixture.
Roll and place in pan.
Cover rolled and stuffed tortillas with more sauce and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Better when reheated.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Cook the first 8 ingredients until the vegetables are tender. Gradually add milk to flour and mix until smooth.
Slowly add milk mixture to vegetables, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Pour flour in bowl.
Add salt and baking soda.
Add butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Also add vanilla extract, eggs and semi-sweet chocolate bits.
Mix until all ingredients are well combined.
Turn oven to 375°.
Bake.
Place on baking sheet and allow to bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: quick key lime pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with electric beater until well mixed.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate until firm. Serve chilled.

title: spiced potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion until tender in water containing salt and chili powder.
Melt fat in skillet; blend in flour and milk gradually.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in potato mixture.
Garnish by sprinkling with parsley.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine drained vegetables and toss lightly.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in saucepan about 20 minutes or microwave-cook on low heat for about 5 minutes.
Let cool and pour over vegetables, stirring gently.
Chill for 24 hours or more.

title: banana split cake
directions: Drain pineapple; use the drained juice as part of liquid for the cake.
Mix and bake cake as directed on package.
Let cool thoroughly.
Slice bananas on top of cake.
Cover with drained pineapple.
Cover this with Cool Whip.
Now cover with coconut and garnish with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken in bite sizes.
Cook in oil until done on medium heat.
When done, add vegetables.
While thawing, add soy sauce and teriyaki sauce.
Stir well while cooking.
Don't overcook. When vegetables are hot through, it is ready to eat.
If you desire more flavor, add a little more sauce.
Serves 4.

title: snow pea quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle bacon, onion and peas in pie shell.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables.
In mixer, beat remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour over vegetables in pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 300°.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until the center is set.

title: speedy rolls
directions: Soak yeast in warm water for 5 minutes.
Add oil, sugar and salt.
Add beaten eggs; beat well.
Add flour; let stand 20 minutes.
Roll out; let rise until double size.
Bake at 325° until light brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peach tea
directions: Mix all in blender to become powder form.
Combine 1 Tbsp. with hot water to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs and add to mixture. Mash bananas.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda together. Add to the sugar mixture and fold in nuts.
Pour into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: 7-can soup
directions: Cook meat, onion, salt and pepper until brown and done in skillet.
Drain off grease after meat is done.
Mix remaining listed ingredients in a big pot.
Put hamburger meat in and cook for about 10 minutes.
This recipe can be cut in half to make a smaller amount.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate cheese and set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan melt margarine over low heat.
Blend in flour.
Add milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Add grated cheese, season and continue to cook, stirring, until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Spread half of the cheese sauce on bottom of shallow 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Slice potatoes and onions.
Arrange slices over cheese sauce.
Spread remaining sauce over top.
Bake until potatoes are tender, about 1 hour.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix following directions on box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 3 (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: johnny appleseed bars
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Mix well.
Spread into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store in tightly covered container at room temperature.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg and beat until smooth and creamy.
Add milk, soda and bananas and mix until well blended. Then add flour, baking powder and salt; beat well.
May add walnuts if desired.
Put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fudge
directions: Spray

8 x 8 or 9 x 9 pan with Pam. Place in oven on low heat, just to melt chocolate chips enough to stir into milk. Stir into milk, add vanilla and salt. Add nuts if desired. Let cool then cut into squares.

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole.
Top with extra cheese. Bake approximately 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: ken's blue cheese potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Boil until almost soft. Pour wine over cooled potatoes.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, Dijon mustard, cider vinegar and Blue cheese.
Pour dressing over potatoes.
Add green onions and celery; mix.

title: picnic cake
directions: Make pudding according to package directions using 2 cups milk.
Add cake mix and blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt 2 large bags of caramels in double boiler.
Sparingly, add 2 or 3 tablespoons water to thin.
Add lots of chopped pecans to stiffen.
Drop on waxed paper.
Freeze or refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut beef very small (I use food processor).
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Add Accent, Worcestershire sauce, 1/2 of beef and all onions to cream cheese.
Mix well and shape into 2 balls and cover with remainder of beef.

title: speedy rolls
directions: Mix sugar, water and yeast together.
Add salt and 2 cups of flour.
Beat two minutes, then add eggs and melted shortening and beat one minute.
Gradually add 4 1/2 cups flour; stir well.
Rest dough for 20 minutes, then roll out.
Spread with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and put in a well-greased pan.
Let rise 40 minutes.

title: lowell inn crescent rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Stir remaining ingredients, except half of flour, into yeast.
Add rest of flour.
Mix until smooth.
Scrape dough from sides of bowl; cover with cloth.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Put grated potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix butter and onions and pour evenly over potatoes.
Combine sour cream and soup and spread over the top.
Sprinkle grated cheese evenly over top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Delicious!

title: broccoli with rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and celery in margarine until vegetables are clear.
Cook broccoli; add to vegetables.
Add soup and cheese.
Stir in the rice; season and mix well.
Put into casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Can be mixed ahead and frozen.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Mix together spaghetti, butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs. Spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add layer of cottage cheese. Mix together hamburger and spaghetti sauce.
Spread on top of cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake another 15 minutes.
let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: Wash berries and boil in the 1 pint water for 15 minutes. Strain through jelly bag.
Four cups juice to 3 cups sugar.
Cook until jelly flakes off of spoon.
Skim and pour into jars.
(Cover with paraffin if you wish.)
Seal with hot rings and lids.

title: new year's cookies(amish recipe)
directions: Combine yeast, warm water and sugar; set aside.
Scald milk and let cool.
Add margarine and salt to milk, then add yeast mixture. Soak raisins in hot water to soften, drain thoroughly and coat with flour to keep the raisins from falling out of dough while deep frying.
Add eggs, flour and raisins in that order.
Dough will be soft.
Let rise until double; deep fry in oil at 375°.
Dip in glaze when done and still hot from frying.

title: three bean - pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain the pasta.
Empty the beans and drain well. Place the beans and pasta in a mixing bowl.
Add the sugar and vinegar; toss until sugar is dissolved.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Toss well and chill at least 2 hours.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: crock-pot taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Cube cheese.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot; heat on low until cheese is melted and mixture is warm, stirring occasionally.
Serve with favorite chips.
This makes a great addition to a Mexican meal or a great snack at parties.

title: pickle hors d'oeuvre
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on each slice of ham.
Place a whole pickle on one end of ham slice and roll up to create a jelly roll shape.
Slice in 1/4 inch slices, discarding the end slices as they tend
to not look as nice.
Serve chilled.

title: pizza dough
directions: Soften yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Set aside.
Pour remaining cup of warm water in a large bowl.
Blend in 2 cups flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir softened yeast and add to flour mixture, mixing well.
Add about 1 cup flour to yeast mixture and beat until very smooth.
Mix in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and allow to rest for about 10 minutes.
Knead for about 8 minutes until dough is smooth and elastic.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients except nutmeg; mix well.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated and flavors are blended, stirring occasionally.
To serve, sprinkle each bowl with a dash of nutmeg. Makes 3 (1-cup) servings.

title: no-fuss barbecued chicken
directions: Shake flour to coat inside of cooking bag.
Add barbecue sauce and orange juice.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add chicken to bag and turn bag to coat chicken with sauce.
Arrange in even layers.
Close bag with nylon tie top.
Makes 6 half-inch slits in top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 251 calories each serving.
Contains 7 grams of fat (less fat if skinless chicken breasts are used).

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine broccoli stems, chicken broth, and onion in a saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add bouillon cubes and cook until dissolved.
Strain and set broth aside.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the cherries.
Put into large bowl and dot with cherries.
Serve cold.

title: italian cheese sticks
directions: Cut Provolone like French fries.
Dip in egg and Italian bread crumbs two times.
Deep fry at 375° until golden brown and cheese melts.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Slice banana into a bowl and mash it with a fork.
Add sugar, salt and milk.
Beat until mixture is foaming.
Now it's ready to serve.
If you like, place a scoop of ice cream in the glass and then pour in the milkshake.
Makes 1 serving.

title: german-style spinach
directions: Heat fat in large skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender. Add flour.
Cook and stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Add water and mix until smooth.
Add spinach.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally as spinach thaws.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: fettucine all fontana candida(origin: italian)
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Add dried fettucine and boil according to package directions.
Saute onions, tomatoes, nuts, basil and garlic in oil for 2 minutes.
Add cream and simmer until thickened, about 10 minutes.
When pasta tests done, drain and toss with sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with Fontana Candida, the light sophisticated wine of Rome.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine vegetables with salt and pepper.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Stir in flour and corn meal, mixing just until moistened. Drop by tablespoons into deep hot oil in large skillet.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: herbed pumpkin rosettes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together the flour and yeast from the package of hot roll mix.
In a medium saucepan, heat and stir pumpkin, water, sugar and the 1/4 cup margarine or butter until warm (120° to 125°).
Add pumpkin mixture and eggs to yeast mixture; mix well.
Stir in as much of the 1/2 cup flour as possible.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead in remaining flour (about 3 minutes).
Cover and let rest 5 minutes. Divide dough into 20 pieces.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In heavy skillet, saute mushrooms in oil.
Remove when tender. Saute onion in same oil until tender.
Remove from skillet. Brown meat quickly on all sides.
Remove; set aside.
Blend flour into oil in skillet.
Gradually add broth; stir constantly until smooth and thick.
Add tomato paste, mustard and sherry; blend well.
Combine sauce with meat, mushrooms and onion in a large saucepan.
Simmer very slowly for 20 to 30 minutes.
Beat yogurt, then blend in 5 minutes before serving.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Pan-fry sausage and stir often.
Drain off grease and mix other ingredients together.
Pour in pan or glass dish.
Cook at 300° to 350° until rice is tender.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix sour cream and Tang with condensed milk.
Pour in pie crust and top with whipped topping.

title: pineapple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat 2 eggs until light and fluffy. Add pineapple (undrained), flour, sugar, brown sugar and soda. Mix these by hand.
Then stir in walnuts and spread contents in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix all ingredients in a buttered dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a large mixing bowl until blended.
Pour into a pie shell and bake approximately 1 hour in a preheated 325° oven or until tests done by inserting a knife in center of pie.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple with juice to a boil. Add Jell-O until melted. Add Cool Whip and buttermilk; mix well. Add nuts; chill until set. Refrigerate overnight. Best to use an electric mixer when mixing ingredients.

title: hot sauce
directions: Dice tomatoes; grind everything up in blender.
Cook over medium heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour into sterile canning jars and seal.
After opening jar, store in refrigerator.

title: fat-free dip
directions: Mix the ingredients with a mixer.
Refrigerate before using for full flavor.

title: angel wing
directions: Cut the margarine into flour as for pie dough.
With a fork, mix together the egg yolks, sour cream and vanilla.
With your hands, form a firm dough.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Divide dough into 4 equal parts, working with one piece at a time; roll out thin on a floured bread board.
Cut into 2-inch squares and cut a slot in the center.
Bake in a 350° oven on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake only until light brown. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: tortilla club sandwich wrap
directions: Warm tortillas.
Layer ingredients in listed order.
Roll up tightly and cut in half on the diagonal.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Place flour in large bowl or pan.
Dissolve salt and sugar in warm (not hot) water.
Add all ingredients and mix well, making a stiff dough.
Grease large bowl and put dough in; turn over (to oil both sides).
Cover with Handi-Wrap and a cloth.
Let stand 8 to 10 hours or until double in bulk.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat with mixer.
Pour into greased (use margarine) 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, omitting butter. Remove from heat and turn into bowl and cool.
Add olives, onions and green pepper to rice.
Drain artichokes, reserving marinade. Add artichokes to rice mixture.
Mix mayonnaise with artichoke marinade and curry powder.
Blend the mayonnaise-artichoke mixture thoroughly with the rice mixture.
Chill 6 hours or overnight to enhance the curry flavor.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add fruit.
Refrigerate until completely chilled.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and molasses slowly.
Bake 2 hours in covered dish in moderate oven at 375°.

title: angel hair stir-fry
directions: Cut the chicken into strips and coat with 1 tablespoon stir-fry sauce.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Cook pasta (don't add salt).
Rinse under cold water and drain.
Combine 1/3 cup stir-fry sauce and water; set aside.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco well; add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, cocoa, soda and salt together 3 times.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; add boiling water last.
Bake in 9 x 13 1/2-inch greased and floured pan at 300° for 15 minutes; then at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes (or until done when tested with toothpick).

title: chicken and beef
directions: Clean and wash chicken.
Rinse dried beef in warm water.
Wrap 2 to 3 slices of dried beef around 1 chicken breast.
Lay the chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mama rains' apple cobbler
directions: Prepare pie crust according to recipe found on Crisco can. Roll dough real thin.
Put around edges of pan, not on the bottom. Place half of the apples in the pan.
Add sugar and butter (just spread around on the apples).
Tear pieces of dough and place among apples.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, bell pepper and onion in a 10-inch skillet until browned.
Drain off fat.
Mix beans and tomatoes; add to meat mixture.
Pour cornbread mix over beans; don't mix.
Put in oven and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Combine vegetables and salt; stir well.
Cover and let stand for 8 hours.
Drain well.

title: grilled meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly until firm.
Using a hamburger grill basket, cover bottom with slices of bacon; top bacon with sliced onion.
Place meat loaf on top of onion, pressing it evenly to all corners of basket.
Lay thinly sliced green pepper rings on top of meat loaf.
Top again with more bacon slices.
Secure cover on basket.
Grill over charcoal about 15 to 20 minutes on each side, or until done to taste.
The grill cover should be used throughout the complete cooking time.

title: bill's onion dip
directions: Soften cream cheese by allowing to stand at room temperature a couple of hours.
Blend in other ingredients with a fork or potato masher.
Use a hand mixer at medium speed to blend until smooth. Serve at room temperature with chips or crackers for dipping.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat all ingredients except crust and filling until stiff. Pour into crust.
Make an opening in center and put in pie filling.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together. Mix the sugar, oil and vinegar. Pour over vegetables. Marinate 24 hours. Pour off liquid. This keeps in the refrigerator several days if covered.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Mix together and microwave for 3 minutes on High, stirring every minute.
Pour over popped corn.

title: chocolate cake(low-fat)
directions: Spray 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, baking soda and salt. In medium bowl, using a fork or wire whisk, mix egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
If desired, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Mix water, salt, sugar, oil and 1 1/2 cups flour well.
Add yeast and mix well.
Gradually add remaining flour, mixing well and kneading until dough is not sticky and is elastic (approximately 5 to 10 minutes).
Place dough in a greased bowl and cover with a towel.
Let rest approximately 1 hour.
Punch dough down in middle.
Divide in half.
Roll each half into rectangle about 1 foot x 3 to 4-inches.
Brush each rectangle with beaten egg.
Layer 3 rows pepperoni and top with shredded cheese. Roll like jelly roll.
