Pinch edge and ends.
Put on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain kidney beans, green French beans and wax beans.
Cut up pepper and onion.

title: red french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and mix well.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare Creamettes| elbow macaroni according to package directions; drain. In large saucepan, melt butter. Add onion; cook until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Blend in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Add cheese; stir until melted. Combine macaroni and cheese mixture; mix well. Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole. Top with breadcrumbs. Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes. Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pie crusts
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add salt, water and vinegar.
Mix well.
Roll into balls using approximately 1 scant cup each of mixture.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Put in Ziploc freezer bags. Freeze.

title: easy eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant.
Cook in small amount of water until tender, but not mushy; drain water.
Cook small amount of onion in margarine until tender.
Combine with eggplant, cheese and bread. Divide 4 eggs and combine yolks with rest of mixture.
Whip whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 360° in a greased pan.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onions are tender. Drain meat and onions. Sprinkle with salt. Prepare gravy mix according to package directions and add to meat mixture. After gravy thickens, add frozen vegetables and basil. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Pour into casserole dish. Prepare seasoned mashed potatoes according to package directions. Fold cheese into mashed potatoes. Spoon potatoes and cheese into a ring on top of meat mixture. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned on top.

title: apricot cookies
directions: Blend flour, salt and butter until crumbly (like pie dough). Blend in cream cheese.
Shape dough into 5-inch square.
Wrap in plastic and chill about 2 hours.
Roll 1/4 of the dough into 12-inch square, cut dough into 2-inch squares and put 1/2 teaspoon apricot filling on each square; fold over opposite corners.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: dilled carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pare carrots with vegetable peeler or scrub them very well with a vegetable brush.
Cut carrots into strips like French fries.
Place carrots in the middle of a piece of heavy-duty foil; dot with margarine and sprinkle with seasonings and water.
Wrap carrots securely in foil and crimp edges.
Bake 45 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients in bowl with fork; beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Run knife around sides of loaf; remove from pan.

title: creole seasoning
directions: Mix; store in tight container.

title: rice pudding(from rice with raisins)
directions: To leftover rice, add an egg or 2 (depending on amount of rice).
Pour in 1/2 cup milk or enough to make almost sloppy. Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake in greased baking dish until done (about 30 minutes at 325°).

title: brown christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in molasses.
Add flour, ginger, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll out on floured surface 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with fancy cookie cutters; decorate with colored sugars.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: butter pecan crunch
directions: Combine crumbs and butter in a bowl.
Pat into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
Beat pudding mixes and milk until well blended, about 1 minute in bowl.
Fold in ice cream and whipped topping.
Spoon over crust.
Sprinkle with crushed candy bars.
Freeze.
Thaw 20 minutes before serving.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Cream butter and cheese together.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and put in cookie press.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Dice and boil potatoes (like mashed potatoes).
Fry bacon while potatoes are cooking until crispy.
Dice up onion and cook in butter until onion is almost clear.
When potatoes are done, drain and put into baking dish.
Then add shredded cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix well into potatoes.
Then add your butter and onions and mix.
Top with bacon and a little bit of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: angel hair primavera pasta
directions: *Suggest organic pastas by Debales (tomato/basil; spinach, garlic, etc.), Michelle's Naturals (same).

title: fruit cocktail cobbler
directions: Pour fruit cocktail (juice and all) onto a well greased oblong cake pan or 2 regular pie plates. Spoon dry cake mix over top of the fruit cocktail. Pour melted oleo over the top of the cake mix. Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until brown. Yields about 12 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spread coconut and pecans in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Do not use Pyrex.)
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, margarine and cream cheese.
Drop by spoonful over cake batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Place pan under cake while baking as it will bubble over. Cool cake in pan, then turn upside down on serving tray.

title: shrimp with angel hair pasta
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Rinse and pat dry.
Coat with olive oil; dust well with salt and pepper and bake in a 350° oven for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; saute in skillet with butter, garlic and wine.
Add tomato sauce and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve over angel hair pasta.

title: zucchini bread
directions: This makes two loaves.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir pudding once or twice while baking.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add molasses, sugar, lightly beaten egg and spices.
Dissolve baking soda in hot coffee, add vinegar and salt. Beat in flour and drop the mixture on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in low oven (325°) for 15 minutes.
Drop 1 teaspoon of batter on sheet for a well rounded cookie; cookie will puff up.

title: lasagne
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir beef, pork, onion and garlic. Drain off excess fat.
In crock-pot, combine beef, pork, onion, garlic, tomatoes, tomato sauce, bouillon, parsley, basil, sugar and salt.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Mix cottage cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, 1/2 teaspoon salt and oregano.

title: aunt mary's molasses cookies
directions: Combine oil, sugar, egg and molasses.
In a separate bowl, mix together the remaining dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture and mix thoroughly.

title: papa's favorite chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top each piece with a slice of cheese.
Combine soup and wine and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Pour melted butter over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked beans(large recipe - 50 to 60 servings)
directions: Bake in a 300° oven for 3 to 4 hours.

title: mom's christmas coffee cake
directions: Take a graham cracker.
Put some M&M's, chocolate, whipped cream, frosting, cherries, sprinkles, jelly or peanut butter on it. Put on a plate.
Eat (don't forget napkins)!

title: brownies(yield: 12 servings)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl.
Add margarine, egg whites and vanilla; beat.
Pour into an 8-inch baking pan, coated with cooking spray.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: escalloped carrots
directions: Cook
carrots,	salt,
onion
and
green
pepper
until carrots
are tender.
Drain.
Make 2 cups light white sauce (1 tablespoon	flour
for
cup
liquid).
(I
save liquid from carrots
to
make
sauce and finish with milk to make 2 cups.) Add 1	cup Cheddar cheese (may be omitted); mix with carrots. Put in greased baking dish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake, uncovered,	in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables according to directions on box. Add remaining 3 ingredients to vegetables; toss and set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute the celery and onions in butter.
Cook broccoli according to box.
Cream the soup and Cheez Whiz.
Drain the vegetables.
Combine all ingredients into casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: halupkies
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, egg, onions, salt, pepper and paprika.
Remove large vein from cabbage leaves and tear large leaves in half.
Place ground beef mixture by spoonful onto cabbage leaf.
Roll.
Cover with tomato juice and sauerkraut. Bake.

title: spanish rice
directions: Follow the directions on box of macaroni and cheese. When done, set at table and eat it or at tv table and eat watching tv. Umm good.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine.
Remove from heat and blend in flour and mustard.
Add milk.
Heat while stirring constantly until it thickens a little and gets smooth.
Add cheese.
Heat until melted.
Stir. Pour over noodles and add bread crumbs.
Bake in heated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until crusty.

title: nannie's potato salad
directions: Cover potatoes with water and boil just until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Let cool completely. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cut margarine in flour and sugar.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; mix in remaining ingredients. Add 1/4 cup of milk to make sticky dough.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans.
Fill pans only half full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cover remaining batter tightly and refrigerate. Batter will keep 2 weeks.

title: egg casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great for brunch!

title: mammaw's chess pie
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and eggs together until well blended. Add flour, cornmeal, vanilla and vinegar. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the chuck with the onion.
Drain the excess fat from the meat.
Meanwhile, prepare the potatoes according to package directions.
In a casserole dish, sprinkle the chuck into the potato mixture.
Bake as directed.
Let cool a little before serving.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs.
Mix in crushed pineapple and juice and melted oleo.
Bake in pastry shell at 275° for about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, margarine, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and crisscross ball with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken cheese lasagne bakefort morgan, colorado
directions: In a 9 X 13 baking dish, place 1/2 of the cooked noodles. Cover with 1/2 sauce, chicken and cheese.
Repeat and end with sauce over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hearty lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella and eggs; set aside.
Brown beef, stirring to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Stir in sauce.
In a large shallow baking dish, layer 1 cup sauce mixture, then noodles and cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles, remaining sauce mixture and Parmesan.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: taco in the round
directions: Cream cheeses together and mix in chili powder.
Place on platter and chill slightly.
Brown meat and drain.
Add taco sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Spread on top of cheese.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and grated cheese (as much as desired).
Serve with corn chips.

title: pastel punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine the 3 chilled juices. Add to this cubed vanilla ice cream and sherbet. Very slowly, add the lemon and lime soda. Serve.

title: super bowl chili
directions: I highly recommend this and it freezes good, too.

title: stir and drop cookies
directions: Add oil, sugar and vanilla to eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and add to oil mixture.
Mix together.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar over cookies and bake at 400° until slightly brown.

title: pancake sandwiches
directions: Slice banana into 1/8-inch slices.
Spread 1 teaspoon peanut butter on each pancake.
Place banana, marshmallows and chocolate chips on top of peanut butter on 1 pancake.
Place other pancake, peanut butter side down, on first pancake and press down gently. Put on paper plate; microwave on High for one minute or until chocolate chips and marshmallows are melted.

title: tante's sour cream waffles
directions: Combine in blender in order listed, blending well after each. Let sit 2 hours to overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine meats, cheese and vegetables as desired.
Add macaroni; season to taste with garlic powder and oregano.
Add salad dressing just prior to serving.

title: julienne of vegetables
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin strips.
Cook until just tender.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Allow to cool.
Cut remaining vegetables in thin strips and combine with potatoes. Combine remaining ingredients together in a jar and shake to mix well.
When ready to serve, pour dressing over.

title: "dirt" pudding
directions: Mix together the vanilla pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
In a separate bowl, mix together the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Crush the Oreo cookies in blender.
Combine the pudding and cream cheese mixtures.
Put 1/2 of the "dirt" (crushed Oreos) in the bottom of a flowerpot or bowl.
Pour in all of the combined mixture.
Put remaining "dirt" on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve, then place a silk flower in "dirt" for effect.
Serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into one pie crust.
Place other crust on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crusts are brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; pat into loaf pan.
Top with desired amount of ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bar-b-q sauce
directions: Add small amount of
water
if needed; put on simmer at least 2 hours or more.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Place flour in plastic bag with the meat; shake to coat meat with flour.
Heat butter in heavy skillet; brown meat.
Remove and cover meat to keep warm.
Add onions and mushrooms; cook slowly for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Return meat to skillet; stir in Worcestershire sauce, sour cream, cream of mushroom soup and Kitchen Bouquet. Bring to boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 4.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer in order listed.
Cover and chill 6 hours.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Coat chicken with flour; shake to remove excess.
In large skillet heat oil and cook chicken cutlets, browning both sides. Remove to plate.
Add broth, butter and lemon juice to skillet. Cook, stirring mixture to a boil.
Return cutlets.
Cover and cook about 2 minutes, basting once with pan juices until cooked through. Before serving, sprinkle with parsley.

title: cheesecake surprise
directions: Combine the crushed graham crackers, walnuts and cinnamon. Grease a
cheesecake pan and dust with graham cracker mixture, reserving unused portion for topping.
Melt marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
Let cool.
Whip the cream cheese and mix in with marshmallows.
Fold in the Cool Whip. Drain the pineapple and mix with the rest of the batter.
Pour half of the batter into the cheesecake pan.
Put the drained strawberries over the mixture and top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle the remaining graham cracker mixture on top. Chill several hours before serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions, then beef.
Add everything else, except sour cream, wine and flour. Cook slowly 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
You may set aside now until ready to eat.
Heat again. Thicken with flour dissolved in reserved mushroom liquid. Add sour cream and wine. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to the directions on box and 1/2 can coconut.
Bake as directed.
While cake is still hot, pierce cake with toothpicks and pour cream of coconut over top.
Allow to cool.
Cover with Cool Whip
and coconut.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Slice chicken into thin strips.
Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper together.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
Heat butter in a skillet and saute chicken until golden brown.
Remove to platter.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Tear apart 2 loaves of frozen bread dough and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour caramel over dough and raise until about double.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Set for a few minutes and turn upside down on cutting board or wax paper.

title: mixed bean bake
directions: Brown sausage lightly.
Drain fat.
Mix all together and place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or put all in your crock-pot and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add green pepper, onion, pineapple, salt and 1 cup pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in remaining pecans and parsley.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: marjo's stew
directions: Cook meat with seasonings until meat is tender.
Add vegetables.
Cover with water and cook until vegetables are tender.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower; add fried bacon, onion, then Mozzarella cheese.
Mix last 5 ingredients and pour over broccoli and cauliflower mixture.
Mix well.
Best when made the night before.

title: hillary's oatmeal crisps
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat shortening, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Add buttermilk, flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add bran flakes.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep for six weeks.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth and drain.
Saute in oil the chopped onions and chopped peppers.
Add mushrooms, stewed tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add chicken pieces (diced).
In casserole, layer spaghetti, layer sauce and layer cheese.
If casserole seems dry, add broth from where spaghetti was cooked.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 10.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° until done.

title: no bake  peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk in a pan.
Boil for 1 minute. In a large bowl measure vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Spoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Keep in airtight container overnight.
Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool.

title: mother's grape-nuts pudding
directions: In baking dish, sprinkle Grape-Nuts into milk.
Let stand while beating eggs well.
Add sugar and vanilla to eggs.
Mix well.
Combine egg mixture with milk and stir together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Pudding should be firm.
Good with Cool Whip.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine all morsels in heavy saucepan over low heat; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add peanuts and stir to coat. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool completely and store at room temperature.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until almost dry.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with soup and onion rings.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 30 to 40 cookies.

title: spiced scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook
tomatoes
until soft; add seasonings.
Boil for 5 minutes;
remove
bay leaf and cloves.
Layer with bread cubes in buttered
baking
dish; cover with butter. Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal brownies
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set oven to 375°.
Cream sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Add egg.
Stir in flour, then oats. Spread into pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: texas bar cake
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix cocoa, sugar and oleo.
Add eggs; beat well. Alternate flour and water.
Add soda and salt.
Beat well.
Add sour cream.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Use sheet cake pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes, until edges are golden brown.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/4-inch cookies.

title: coconut custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg, milk and coconut.
Mix well.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Pour custard mixture into dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: popeye(rolled dough)
directions: Mix all ingredients to make stiff dough; knead, roll out and cut into squares.
Drop into boiling beef or chicken broth.
Cook 10 minutes with lid on; uncover and cook 10 minutes with lid off.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip with sugar until dressing tastes sweet.
Thin with half and half cream until consistency of very heavy cream. Pour over remaining ingredients and it is ready to serve.
Can be served with hard-boiled eggs or deviled eggs and toast points. Quick and easy lunch.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Chop entire bunch of onions, including green tops.
Mix all ingredients together.
Delicious with vegetable dippers or snack foods.

title: ground-nut soup(african)
directions: Brown chicken and onions in large saucepan until golden.
Salt to taste.
Add just enough cold water to cover chicken and add tomatoes.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 15 minutes. Remove tomatoes; scoop out pulp and add pulp to stock.
Mix peanuts or peanut butter into smooth cream with hot stock from saucepan.
Add water and peppers.
Season to taste.
Cook slowly until oil rises to the top of soup.
If chicken becomes tender before oil rises, remove chicken to prevent disintegration. Return to pot when soup is cooked.
Serves 6.

title: very berry cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and 1 cup boiling water.
Mix cranberry sauce with the other cup of boiling water.
Mix the two together and chill until thick.
Stir in chopped pecans to this and pour half of mixture into a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Let set until firm.

title: aunt bea's peanuts
directions: Combine sugar and water in large pan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Stir constantly.
Add peanuts.
Continue cooking and stirring until all syrup has been absorbed.
Spread on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in oven at 300° for 1 hour, stirring four times.
Do not double recipe.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Make mashed potatoes. Saute onions in margarine and butter.
In a large casserole dish, arrange the following in layers in this order:
1/2 onion mixture, 1/2 macaroni, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 mashed potatoes, 1/2 macaroni, 1/2 cheese, the remaining 1/2 mashed potatoes with the other 1/2 onion mixture on top.
Cover and bake at 340° for 40 minutes.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Cook beans; drain and reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onion.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Remove from heat; stir in milk and reserved 1/2 cup liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in ham, eggs, cheese, pimento and parsley.
Place beans in baking dish and cover with ham sauce. Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine oil, brown sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, egg whites, oat bran, oatmeal and wheat germ; mix with spoon to moisten.
Stir in blueberries.
Fill paper-lined muffin tins 3/4 full with batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.
Cool and serve.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt margarine and allow to cool.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs to cooled margarine.
Add dry ingredients to margarine mixture.
Mix well and chill overnight.
Form into 1-inch balls (dough will be very stiff).
Roll balls in granulated sugar and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: ripe olive cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold with crackers. May be served hot by spreading on crackers then bake at 250° for 20 minutes.
This spread will freeze well.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine, oil and marshmallows.
Pour mixture over popped popcorn.
Add M&M's candies and peanuts; mix well.
Pack into well-greased tube pan.
Let set until firm; turn out onto a plate.

title: artillery punch(shared by dr. r. b. congleton)
directions: Mix well and put in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, pour over ice and add 1 quart club soda.
This makes a 45 proof drink and will serve 30 people, 2 drinks each.
Watch out.

title: molten chocolate cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease 12 muffin cups. Combine butter and chocolate chips in a double boiler. Cook, stirring continually until melted. Let stand to cool slightly. Combine eggs and sugar in a large bowl. Beat with an electric mixer at medium speed until thickened, about 5 minutes. Add flour gradually, beating at low speed. Add chocolate mixture and beat until thick and glossy, about 3 minutes. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake cakes for 5 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, peanuts and salt in heavy pot. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until peanuts have light parched color. Remove from heat; stir in soda gently but quickly. At once, pour on buttered cookie sheet. Spread and let cool. Break into pieces.

title: hot buttered rum(beverages)
directions: Throughly mix butter and sugars.
Gradually mix in softened ice cream until smooth.
Keep the mixture in the freezer until needed.
Place 1 to 3 heaping tablespoons of mixture into a mug. Add desired amount of rum.
Fill the mug with boiling water.
Stir well.
Top with nutmeg or cinnamon.

title: potato soup
directions: On low heat, cook potatoes, onion, garlic and salt and pepper with just enough water to cover; cook until done. Add butter, soups, cream cheese and milk to potatoes. Cook on low heat until thick. Garnish with shredded cheese, bacon bits or chives if desired and serve.

title: fudge
directions: Mix and boil sugar, cream, butter and cocoa until thick.
Keep mixing so it doesn't burn to the bottom of the pot and test for thickness by dropping some in a small glass of cold water.
When it forms a hard ball, take off stove and add Marshmallow Fluff and mix, then add walnuts.
Put in buttered pan and put in cool place.

title: cooking a country ham
directions: First, wash that mold off with warm water (for you "city slickers," ham mold does not mean it's no good).
Now, cut off the hock end (that's the smallest end) with meat saw.
Put ham in cooker (or lard stand) and let soak overnight.
You don't have to do this if you're cooking a "store bought" ham.
Pour off water and put fresh water over ham with brown sugar.
Let ham come to boil and boil for 1 hour.

title: creole dip
directions: Saute meat until loose but not brown.
Add bell pepper and onions; cook until soft.
Add hot sauce to taste, pimentos and garlic powder.
Add the Velveeta cheese, cut into pieces.
Stir until melted.
Serve hot.

title: weight watchers fruit salad
directions: Heat applesauce to bubble; remove from heat.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Combine with pineapple in serving bowl.
Add 7-Up.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes a lot.
Recipe can easily be cut in half.

title: united fund cookies
directions: Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and butter.
Add the condensed milk, flour, chopped walnuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet; bake for 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.
Keep the cookie dough mixture at room temperature for easier handling.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a greased tube pan.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Place cinnamon and cloves in percolator basket.
Add remaining ingredients to percolator pot.
Perk until hot.
Serve.
May be cooled, refrigerated and heated as needed.
Yield:
9 cups.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar together.
Crumble half of mixture into bottom of pie crust.
Prepare pudding as directed and pour on top of mixture.
Top pudding with whipped topping and remaining crumbles.

title: baked beans
directions: Add chopped green or red sweet pepper to give a good taste. Mix onions, pepper, beans and ketchup.
Pour into a baking dish; arrange bacon on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chili
directions: Chop onion.
Brown hamburger and onion together. Drain fat. Add tomato soup and kidney beans. Stir.
Add chili powder (more or less to taste).
Simmer for 10 minutes on low heat.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites until very stiff. Gradually beat in sugar.
Fold in chips and walnuts.
Grease 2 cookie sheets and put 30 cookies on each.
When oven has reached 400°, quickly put trays in oven and shut oven off.
Do not open oven for 6 hours or let remain overnight.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream margarine with sugar. Beat in the eggs; fold in milk, bread cubes and pineapple. Stir well. Spray 9 x 13 Pyrex baking dish with Pam or other spray. Pour mixture into baking dish.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple, pulp and juice.
This will cool the gelatin enough to add strawberries, bananas and pecans.
Mix well and pour into individual molds or oblong molds.
Refrigerate to congeal. Top with whip cream.

title: madonna church pierogi
directions: Water in which potatoes were cooked for filling is saved and used in making dough.

title: honey pecan butter
directions: Combine in food processor (or mixer) and process until well blended. Spoon into bowl and refrigerate.

title: cauliflower and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil cauliflower and broccoli until barely tender.
Melt the butter; add and blend with the flour.
Slowly add the warm milk. Cook over low heat until thick and smooth; stirring constantly. Continue to cook as you add the cheese, cook only until the cheese is melted.
Pour over the vegetables.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put browned ground beef in the bottom of a casserole dish. Spread corn over ground beef.
Spread potatoes over corn and bake at 375° until potatoes turn gold on top.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: homemade butter
directions: Put cream in containers and begin shaking.
Keep shaking.
You will see the liquid turn to solid and it will sound like a rock is inside of container.
When you open lid, all cream will be in a ball.
Place butter ball in chilled ice water, excess cream will float away.
Chill and serve.
Great fun.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Add cucumbers and bring to a boil until they turn to a transparent color.
Can and seal.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion.
Drain off fat.
Mix together catsup, salt, mustard and vinegar; stir into meat.
Mix beans together to create the "Calico" look.

title: penn-dutch green beans
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet; drain and crumble.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of drippings; add onion and saute until tender. Blend in cornstarch, salt and mustard.
Drain beans; keep 1/2 of liquid.
Stir reserved liquid into skillet; cook.
Stir occasionally with wooden spoon until thickened and bubbly. Stir in sugar and vinegar.
Add beans.
Heat until bubbly hot.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and egg.

title: chili con carne(yields 4 cups)
directions: Wash beans, cover with water and soak overnight.
Cover with additional water and cook until tender.
Mix flour, onion, garlic and meat; saute in a low salt fat until brown.
Add beans, chili pepper and tomatoes to the mixture.
Simmer until liquid is consistency of thin sauce or about 30 minutes.

title: onion soup au gratin(low-cal)
directions: In 1-quart nonstick saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onions. Cook over medium-high heat until onions are transparent.
Add 1/2 cup water, the dissolved broth and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce to low and simmer 15 minutes.
Preheat broiler.
Set 2 flameproof bowls on baking sheet.
Ladle half of the soup into each bowl. Top each with a slice of bread and then half the cheese.
Broil until cheese has melted, about 2 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Sprinkle sugar over sauerkraut and allow to stand 1/2 hour. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover well and allow to set 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.
Makes 6 servings.
Keeps well for up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low all day. Serve over noodles.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet.
Cut cabbage into thin strips. Cook on low heat until cabbage is tender.
Very good!

title: crabmeat rolls
directions: Melt the butter and saute the scallions and onion until onion is translucent.
Do not brown.
Add the garlic and cook a few minutes over medium-low heat.
Add crabmeat and bread crumbs and toss together.
Remove from heat and stir in ginger, parsley and cayenne pepper; cool the mixture to lukewarm.
Add egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap; set aside.
Cut the sheets of packaged dough into fourths; immediately cover with a damp towel to keep dough from drying out.
As you work, keep unused layers of dough covered.
Place piece of cut dough on a work surface and brush it with melted butter.
Place another piece on top; brush it with butter and continue layering and buttering until there are four layers.

title: jell-o salad
directions: Let Jell-O chill to 2/3 consistency. Mix Jell-O with blender until smooth. Stir in (by hand) cottage cheese, pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts. Place in bowl and chill.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix 1/3 cup soup, 1/4 cup milk, onion and parsley.
Dip chicken in soup mixture, then roll in stuffing.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Drizzle butter on chicken.
Bake for 1 hour in 400° oven.
Combine remaining soup and milk; heat.
May serve over chicken.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Wash green tomatoes, slice and pack in jars.
Put 1 teaspoon salt to each quart.
Cover with cold water.
Put on rings and flats.
Do not seal.
Put in cold pack and boil 2 minutes.
Take out and seal.

title: sherbet smoothies
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately in chilled glasses.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in large saucepan.
Heat until boiling point.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat; add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread in desired pans; cool.

title: campfire custard
directions: Place eggs in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except marshmallows and blend well.
Cook over medium-hot campfire, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add marshmallows and cook until they dissolve.

title: caramel-pecan sticky buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add milk, 1/4 c. sugar, oil, salt and 1 1/4 c. flour.
Beat on medium speed for 2-3 minutes or until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 6-8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down and turn onto lightly floured surface.
Roll into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread butter to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over butter.
Roll up, jelly-roll style, starting with a long side.
Pinch seam to seal and cut into 12 slices.
Combine brown sugar and cream; pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Place rolls, cut side down, over pecans; cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until well browned.
Cool for 1 minute before inverting onto serving platter.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast into lukewarm water.
Add to ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator until needed.
Make into rolls and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: turkey soup
directions: Place carcass and water in a large soup kettle.
Add onions, bay leaves, salt, pepper, parsley, thyme and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove carcass.
Add vegetables.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add cubed turkey meat.
For more seasoning, add 1 teaspoon poultry seasoning.
Makes 14 cups.

title: nut rolls (small)
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Work in shortening like pie dough. Dissolve yeast in evaporated milk as directed on yeast package. Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Keep working and kneading until mixture forms a shiny ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 8 hours or overnight.

title: milky way cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease Bundt pan.
In top of double boiler, melt candy bars and butter.
Cool.
Beat eggs, adding sugar and vanilla.
In a large measuring cup, add soda to buttermilk. Add flour and buttermilk to egg mixture.
Stir in candy mixture and fold in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy st. pete coffee cake
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together for 10 minutes.
Mix together remaining ingredients and set aside 3 tablespoons.
Fold rest into cake.
Pour into ungreased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle sugar mix onto top of cake.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: mayonnaise or salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "pumpkin" cupcakes
directions: *Tint 1 cup icing green and the remainder tint orange.

title: seeley-azzo
directions: Several hours ahead of time, thaw frozen bread dough according to directions on package.
Brown beef, sausage, onions and peppers in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Drain.
Add ham, pepperoni, Mozzarella cheese and hot pepper cheese.
Add enough spaghetti sauce to make mixture pourable but not runny.
Set over low heat.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix ingredients and form into balls. Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Even if you hate spinach, you'll love these!
Makes 36.

title: oil salad dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients and shake well.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Cream well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavor, if desired.
If butter is of good flavor, omit vanilla.
Add sifted flour alternately with buttermilk to which soda is added, 1/3 teaspoon to each 1/2 cup.
Batter should be smooth.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan which has been greased and floured for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: sweet berry bread
directions: Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
In medium bowl, cream butter, sugar and almond extract. Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each one.
Grease an 8 x 4 x 2 loaf pan, then line with waxed paper and grease paper.
Turn batter into pan, smoothing top evenly with spoon. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let bread cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Then turn out on wire rack; peel off paper and cool completely.

title: fluffy cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk or electric mixer until blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping and spoon into pie crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil and blend.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla and mix well.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: honey-baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Arrange chicken skin side up in shallow baking pan.
Mix honey, mustard, lemon juice, garlic, or onion powder, and curry powder.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 400°
for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Uncover. Baste meat with sauce.
Bake uncovered another 10 minutes. Yield: 4 servings.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Bring liquid to boil.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Let boil until almost red and syrupy.
Fill jars and seal.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
You can put whole pecans on top to make it look pretty.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Add yeast to water; set aside to soften.
Heat milk in large pan until bubbles form at edges.
Add salt, sugar and oil, then cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour; stir to make a smooth batter.
Add remaining flour; stir to form dough.
Knead dough on floured board until smooth.
Let it rise in a greased, covered pan until double in bulk.
Fold dough down; let rest 5 minutes. Divide dough in half.
Roll one portion at a time on floured board to make an oblong layer, 3/8-inch thick.
Spread layer with melted butter, then with combined sugar and cinnamon.
Roll dough lengthwise; cut in 1-inch slices.
Let slices rise in greased pans until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let baked rolls set in pan for 2 minutes, then remove them to cooling rack.

title: pauline gilliam's red cinnamon apples
directions: Put sugar, ,water and cinnamon in a very large pan.
Let cinnamon and sugar dissolve; bring mixture to a boil. Drop peeled and cored apples into mixture.
Cook until tender.
May be stored in refrigerator several days before serving.
A very pretty dish for Christmas.

title: stir fried pork lo mein
directions: Spray wok with cooking spray.

title: cowboy cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and shortening together; put 2/3 cup of mixture into separate bowl and save.
Mix rest of ingredients with remaining mixture.
Pour mixture into cake pan and top with saved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients at low speed 5 minutes. Change to high speed and beat 15 minutes.
Pile in shell and freeze.
Serve from freezer.
(Do not defrost pie.)

title: quick and easy fudge(microwave recipe)
directions: Line bottom of an 8-inch square baking dish with wax paper; set aside.
Combine first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole. Stir gently.
Add butter; microwave, uncovered, on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in prepared dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Yield:
Double recipe for full bowl of fudge.

title: elegant raspberry chocolate pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Spoon in ice cream, stirring until melted and smooth.
Chill until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: autumn currant pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in sugar, vinegar and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate (350°).
Bake 30 minutes longer; cool.

title: roast
directions: Salt, pepper and flour all sides of roast.
On top of stove, brown roast on all sides in about 2 tablespoons of oil in heavy pot.
(I use Club Aluminum roaster.)
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix on top of meat.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups water.
Cover.
It will steam and moisten soup mix.
Bake, covered, at 425° for about an hour. Uncover and let all the water bake out until bottom of pot is brown (almost burned).
Add water and continue baking until roast is done.
Remove from pot and slice. Replace slices in pot.
Add water to have juice for meat to absorb.
Bake, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a pie plate.
Put broccoli on bottom and cheese on top.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-onion bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook and drain onions.
(Cook each in boiling salted water until tender.)
In saucepan, melt half the margarine. Blend in flour, salt and a dash of pepper.
Add milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly. Reduce heat. Blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Put vegetables in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce mixture over.
Mix slightly.
Top with shredded cheese.
Mix the remaining butter (melted) with the bread crumbs. Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Save 1/2 cup flour to roll out rolls.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour batter into the butter.
Add cherries sweetened to taste.
Add about 1 1/2 cups sugar and lemon juice.
Do not stir or mix.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or plain.

title: southern okra(microwave)
directions: Place okra, green pepper, onion and water in a microwave-safe casserole. Cook, covered, 5 to 7 minutes until vegetables are done to your taste. Add tomatoes, sugar and pepper, stirring gently. Cook, covered, 2 more minutes or until heated through. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Grate cheese.
Bring water, wine, butter and seasonings to a boil.
Add cheese and set into double boiler.
(Use stainless steel or ceramic pot.)
Stir thoroughly with wooden spoon until cheese melts into a smooth, heavy sauce.
If fondue seems too thick, add more wine; if too thin, add more cheese.
Dice rye or French bread into 2-inch squares and brown lightly in oven.
Use for fondue.
You must have double boiler or cheese will burn.

title: sweet and sour chicken glaze
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix jam, soup mix and dressing.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Turn once to coat.

title: sugar balls
directions: Combine vanilla wafers, confectioners sugar, cocoa powder and nuts.
Stir in juice and corn syrup.
Add a little water (about 1 1/4 teaspoons), if necessary, to form little balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.

title: easy cheese-stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells.
Rinse in cool water.
Drain well.
Combine egg, cottage cheese, Parmesan, Mozzarella, parsley and oregano.
Spoon about 1/4 cup in each shell.
Place shells in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over shells.
Bake, covered, at 375° for about 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: shrimp balls
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and shape into small balls.
Roll in chopped parsley.
Spear with pretzel sticks.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into the graham cracker crust. Freeze.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.
Easy dessert to make.

title: kraut reubens
directions: Toss kraut with caraway seed and garlic powder; set aside. Spread bread with dressing.
Top 8 slices bread with corned beef, kraut mixture, cheese and remaining 8 slices bread.
Brush melted butter on both of sandwiches.
Grill until cheese is melted.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook pepperoni in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Saute onion in 1 1/2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix remaining margarine with spaghetti.
Put spaghetti into 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover spaghetti with 8 ounces sauce.
Add 1/2 each of the Cheddar cheese, pepperoni, sausage and Mozzarella cheese. Add mushrooms and onions; sprinkle with oregano, basil and remaining cheese, pizza sauce and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger noodle dish(casserole dish)
directions: Brown hamburger (broken into small pieces, crumbled).
Add dash of garlic salt or fresh garlic (squeezed).
When brown, pour tomato sauce over meat.
Cover and let simmer 20 minutes, checking and stirring now and then (cover is optional).
In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream, green onions, salt, pepper and sugar.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla extract. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes; invert onto serving plate.
Spoon Creamy Chocolate Glaze over top of warm cake, allowing it to drizzle down sides.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix thawed strawberries and crushed pineapple in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dump cake mix evenly over mixture of fruit.
Put melted butter over cake mix.
Add walnuts.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potato bake
directions: Spread 4 cups potatoes in bottom of a greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour half the mixture over potatoes.
Repeat layers.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Slowly cook celery, onion and green pepper in bacon drippings until light brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Add bay leaf, tomatoes, tomato paste and sugar. Mix well.
Add salt, pepper, curry powder and a generous sprinkle of Louisiana Creole seasoned salt.
Cook very slowly for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Fry ground beef and drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Wash green peppers well, cut in half and blanch in hot water for 5 minutes.
Add meat mixture; top with tomato sauce.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake nutty oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil cocoa, sugar, milk and butter.
Let mixture boil one additional minute, stirring constantly.
Add crunchy peanut butter; stir.
After peanut butter melts, add oatmeal. Stir well.
Quickly spoon out onto waxed paper and let cookies harden.
Cook on medium heat.
If heat is too high, cookies cook too fast and will not harden.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter zucchini cake
directions: Mix eggs, peanut butter, oil and sugar.
Add pineapple and dry ingredients.
Add zucchini and raisins.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: "old buckeye" pound cake(easy, delicious and all done with the mixer)
directions: Cream together butter or oleo and sugar. Beat eggs into this mixture, one at a time. Sift in a mixture of flour and mace and beat the batter until it is smooth. All beating may be done with the mixer, using slow speed when adding the flour mixture. Turn the batter into a buttered tube pan (I use Pam spray) and bake in a moderate oven for 1 hour. Cool in the pan for 10 to 15 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or pour desired flavor of icing over the cake.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Combine
the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the
margarine
until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Combine the egg and milk and then add to the flour mixture all at once. Stir
dough until it follows a fork around the bowl. Turn out
on a lightly floured surface.
Knead gently with the heel of
your hand
about 20 strokes.
Roll dough out and cut 3/4 inch thick. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Use Jell-O to give desired color for punch.
Let cool.
Add pineapple juice and lemonade. Add ice cubes.
Sugar may be added, if desired.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Yields 50 servings.

title: colonel-style fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken dry.
Make a paste of salad dressing mix, flour, salt, lemon juice and butter.
Brush to coat chicken evenly. Stack pieces in bowl, cover and refrigerate several hours.
About 1 1/2 hours before serving, heat 1/2-inch of oil in a skillet.

title: dump salad
directions: Do not dissolve gelatin.
Add dry straight from package to the pineapple and cottage cheese, stirring to blend.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.
Mix 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: idaho potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes whole with skins.
When done, let cool and then place in refrigerator.
Butter a 3-quart size casserole dish. Grate the cold potatoes (remove skins first) on small side of grater.
Spread in the buttered casserole dish.
In a saucepan, heat butter and half and half until hot.
Pour over grated potatoes and add seasoning.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and then with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
(If pimentos are used, add by sprinkling over grated potatoes prior to adding half and half.)

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Saute garlic in hot oil, but do not let it brown, or it will turn bitter.
Add the juice from the two cans of clams and the white wine to the skillet.
Simmer briskly for 3 to 4 minutes to reduce the liquid.
Reduce the liquid. Reduce heat.
Toss the clams in the liquid and heat through.
Add salt and pepper and sprinkle with parsley, if you have it.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine both mixtures together and put in a 2-quart buttered pan.
Mix 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine and 1 cup of cornflake crumbs; sprinkle them on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 people.
Can be frozen.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Dice potatoes.
Cook until just tender in the 2 cups of water.
Do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat through over medium heat, stirring often.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients, using enough flour to make a dough stiff enough to roll out.
Place on floured cloth; roll out and cut with doughnut cutter.
Deep fry.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Spread beans over bottom of 10-inch glass pie plate; layer remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chile gravy
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Add chile powder (amount to taste).
Put 1 cup water in hamburger, stir to mix in small bowl.
Put flour in bowl.
Add water to make paste and add to hamburger until desired thickness.
Put over bread or boiled potatoes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of spring-pan.
Dust with graham crackers; spread remaining crumbs on bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese until smooth.
Add egg whites.
Add sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
After baking for 25 minutes at 350°, remove from oven and add topping (sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla).
Put back in oven and bake at 475° for 5 minutes.
Let stand in refrigerator for 3 days!

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix with salt and pepper.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: end of the trail beans
directions: Put beans in baking dish.
Saute onion and garlic in the oil. Add rest of ingredients and heat.
Pour over beans in dish and stir to mix.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: taco sauce
directions: Put all vegetables in blender.
Use a little tomato juice to start.
Blend; mix well.
Pour into pan and boil for 15 minutes. Fill hot, sterilized jars and seal.
I always put jars in a boiling bath for 15 to 20 minutes.
Make sure the lids have sealed.

title: cheese snack
directions: Mix cheese and butter.
Add rest of ingredients. Shape into 1-inch balls. Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Slice and bake in a 375° oven on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.

title: hot puppie creole
directions: Cut hot puppies or hot dogs into 1/2-inch pieces.
Heat oil. Add hot puppies or hot dogs and stir until brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn with liquid, chili powder, salt and onion.
Heat to boiling; reduce and simmer 10 minutes.
While sauce simmers, cook macaroni.
Then mix together.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: In a large stock pot, boil the potatoes (with skins on) until done.
Drain.
Peel potatoes and cut into 2 x 1-inch squares.
Set aside.

title: advent cookies(adventski kolacoco, croation)
directions: Beat the sugar, eggs and lemon rind together for 15 minutes until light and fluffy.
Add flour and walnuts.
Mix.
Drop by spoonful on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pizza bread
directions: Lightly grease (or Pam) a cookie sheet.
Cut sandwich meat into small pieces; cut pepperoni in half, cube cheeses and set aside. Prepare bread according to the directions on the box.
After the bread has rested for five minutes, cut into two equal pieces.
Roll out one piece of dough in a rectangle shape, try not to get it too thin.
Spread lightly with melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with garlic salt or garlic powder.
Cover with half of the sandwich meat, half of the pepperoni, half of the Cheddar cheese and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Roll the bread like a jelly roll; be sure to tuck in all edges.
Place on one end of the cookie sheet.
Do the same to the other piece of the bread dough.
Be sure that the loaves are at opposite ends of the pan; you don't want them touching as they will "leak" if they do.
The bread should rise until doubled in size.
After it has risen, bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until it is golden brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients to meal consistency, then mix remaining ingredients.
Add the liquid mixture to the flour mixture and blend.
Roll out into circle and place in pie plate. Fill with your favorite pie filling.
Makes 2 double 9-inch pies or 3 double 8-inch pies.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Beat eggs with sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add to butter in skillet.
Increase heat.
Cook until thick or mixture pulls away from skillet.
Add nuts, dates and cherries. Let cool about 15 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies.
Drop one spoonful on coconut and roll in ball.
Put in icebox and let set at least 12 hours.
Makes pretty Christmas cookie, but good anytime.

title: chinese clusters
directions: Place chocolate and butterscotch morsels in 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Heat in Radarange oven on Cookmatic level 6 for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper. Let set until firm.
Yields 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream flour, butter and confectioners sugar together.
Press evenly into bottom of ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy.
Pour onto hot crust.
Bake for about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Yield:
16 squares.

title: pound cake
directions: Melt butter and Crisco; mix with sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in cold oven turned on to 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: john's favorite crispy krinkles
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter in microwave.
Stir in Crispix, pretzels and nuts.
Place in large Tupperware container; shake powdered sugar through mixture.
Store in airtight container and refrigerate.
Yum, yum, yum!

title: lentil soup with vegetables
directions: Into large saucepan, put lentils, water, onion and celery stalk.
Bring to a boil and add oil.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
Add carrot, potato, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: caramel german chocolate cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake according to directions in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 20 minutes. While hot, sprinkle on pecans and the chocolate chips. Bake 20 minutes more at 350°. While baking, melt 1 bag of caramels, one stick oleo and 1/2 cup milk together in double boiler or microwave. Pour this over the top of the cake when it comes from the oven.

title: pear honey
directions: Grind pears through food chopper.
Add sugar and boil 50 minutes.
Add pineapple and boil 25 minutes longer.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: potato cheese dish
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in margarine 5 to 10 minutes, until clear.
Add flour and stir.
Add heated milk and pimento. Stir until thick.
Add potato.
Pour into greased baking dish. Top with cheese.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups soft bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Leave room for the dish to bubble.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook potato until done. Mash well. Add sugar slowly until mixture is stiff enough to roll on dough board. Roll on sugar to keep from sticking. Roll 1/4-inch thick. Spread top with peanut butter. Roll up. Chill in waxed paper. Cut into squares.

title: bacon and cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash mushrooms thoroughly.
In blender, combine mushrooms stems with remaining ingredients.
Process until finely chopped.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 20 appetizers.

title: four layer pie
directions: Melt the oleo.
Mix the flour and nuts.
Press in Pyrex dish. Bake at 375° until brown, about 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chocolate-dipped apricots
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and add apricots.
Gently simmer 2 minutes. Remove apricots with a slotted spoon and let cool on waxed paper. Combine 1/3 of the chocolate, shortening and brandy with 2 tablespoons of water in a small saucepan.
Heat to melt chocolate, stirring smooth.
Add remaining chocolate and stir until melted. Dip apricots halfway into chocolate and place on waxed paper to cool.
Store, covered, in the refrigerator.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and salt.
Melt chocolate and butter together.
Cool.
Add to egg mixture along with flour and pecans. Bake at 325° in greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1 tablespoon butter. Add in order the water and bouillon cubes; bring to a boil.
Add broccoli, noodles and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add milk and seasonings.
Heat through.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into a roll.
Sprinkle roll with paprika.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and raisins in large bowl.
Blend together the mayonnaise, lemon juice, 1/4 teaspoon salt, curry powder and dash of pepper.
Toss lightly with chicken mixture. Chill.
Just before serving, add cashew nuts and toss.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple bars
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil, then in a separate bowl sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture. Fold in apples and nuts.
Use mixer at low speed and mix for 1 minute.
Pour into a greased and floured pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cover with powdered sugar.

title: georgia powell's country style chili with beans
directions: Mix beef, onion, pepper and salt in pot.
Cover and cook over low to medium heat for approximately 45 minutes.
Add chili powder, tomatoes and beans.
If necessary, add water.
Simmer for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Melt margarine in pot and saute onion.
Add flour and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add chicken, peas and carrots, salt and pepper to taste.
Put 1 pie crust in bottom of pie plate, then add mixture.
Top with second pie crust; make little slits in top to vent.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown.

title: quick peach crisp
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, spice and margarine until crumbly. Pour peaches into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and sugar.
Spread crumb mixture over top.
Bake at 375° in gas oven about 30 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: In one bowl, mix eggs, oil, sugar, carrots and vanilla.
Into another bowl, sift dry ingredients.
Mix the two together and beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° fo 45 minutes or until tests done.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pimentos, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Mix and bake in covered shallow 1-quart casserole for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Place remaining Swiss cheese and onions on top and bake uncovered for about 5 minutes or until brown on top.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boiling the cocoa, oleo and water.
Remove from heat. Add the remaining ingredients; beat well with mixer.
Pour into jelly roll pan.
(No need to grease or flour.) Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: raisin date pudding
directions: Boil the first two ingredients together.
Let cool; pour in bottom of pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl, stir well.
Gently toss spinach and strawberries in large bowl.
Arrange on 8 individual plates.
Drizzle poppy seed mixture over each salad.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Prepare crust according to package directions.
Press pecans into bottom of unbaked crust.
Bake and allow to cool.

title: tuie's meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt.
Add sugar teaspoon at a time while beating.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: wooden wedding cake
directions: This cake is supposed to be served on your fifth wedding anniversary, when the appropriate gift is wood.

title: minestra con i finocchi(fennel soup)
directions: Clean the fennel bulbs and discard the stalks and tough outer layers.
Slice the bulbs thinly, then chop finely.
Place in a saucepan with the oil and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Pour in the broth, season with salt and pepper.
Bring to simmer. Simmer for 30 minutes, then pour the soup into a tureen.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks. Add syrup, vanilla and pecans.
Stir well. Fold in egg whites. Pour into unbaked large pie shell; in Pyrex works well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness with toothpick in center; toothpick clean, pie done.

title: maple syrup muffins
directions: Mix eggs, liquids and margarine.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until just moistened.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: penuche frosting
directions: Stir brown sugar into melted butter.
Boil and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Stir in milk and cool.
Stir in 1 3/4 to 2 cups powdered sugar (enough for spreadable consistency).
Use on Spice Cake.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix.
Add alternately the wet and dry ingredients.
Flatten a walnut sized piece of dough, using a flat glass which has been dipped in sugar. With a spoon indent a space in the cookie middle; fill with jelly.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, or until firm.

title: shirley's cookies
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar, cocoa and milk. Cook 3 minutes until soft-ball stage is reached in water.
Add oats. Drop onto buttered wax paper.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix in a saucepan and bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Mix in bowl the flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well the eggs, soda, vanilla and sour milk.
Add all the ingredients together.
Pour into a well-greased jelly roll pan. Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: party meatballs
directions: Roll ground beef into small balls; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in a large pot.
Add meatballs. Simmer on low until meatballs are done, 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes about 100 meatballs.

title: impossible ham and cheese pie
directions: Grease pie plate (10 x 1/2-inch).
Heat oven to 400°. Sprinkle ham, onion and cheese in bottom of pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth; pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown, or until knife comes out clean when inserted, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bourbon pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine eggs, sugar, butter or oleo, syrup, vanilla and bourbon.
Sprinkle chips and pecans in bottom of pie shell.
Pour in filling.
Bake for 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let set for 30 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Put in bundles of 6 to 10 green beans and wrap with bacon slice.
Secure with a toothpick.
Melt margarine with brown sugar. Add soy sauce; heat until all blended.
Spray dish with Pam. Arrange bundles of green beans in dish; pour sauce over and cover. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *Or, use 2 cans cream of chicken soup.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In large casserole dish, layer chicken, then mixed vegetables. Mix soups together and add onion, if desired.
Spread mixture over mixed vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise, flour and milk.
Mixture will be thin but will thicken as it cooks.
Spread over casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Use 1/3 cup and fill cup with hot water.

title: betsy's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a medium bowl; set aside. Cream together sugars and shortening.
Fold in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients 1/3 at a time; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown chops in margarine; remove from skillet. Add additional butter, if necessary, and saute chopped onion until soft, but not brown. Prepare stuffing mix as directed. Add onion. Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread mixture on bottom of pan. Place pork chops on top of stuffing mixture. Cover chops with applesauce and cinnamon. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: corned beef salad
directions: I usually do not use that much onion.

title: texas hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add beans and cook 5 more minutes.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Cover with batter and bake in oven for 20 minutes or until batter is done.
Good.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put fruit in large bowl.
In a separate small bowl, mix dry pudding and dry Tang with the pineapple juice.
Stir until smooth and pour over fruit.
Refrigerate.
Stir before serving.

title: fast and flameless candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil on medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Add corn flakes and stir until all are coated with syrup mixture. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper to cool.

title: bobbie's grandmom's rice pudding
directions: Rinse
rice before cooking.
Cook rice in the 4 cups of water. Remove from heat as soon as water is cooked up.

title: baked vidalia sweet onions
directions: Core a large Vidalia sweet onion for each person.
Add salt, pepper and a generous pat of butter to hollow.
Wrap in foil; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on size of onion.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add in pretzels.
Marinate overnight.
Bake on foil pan for 5 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar, vanilla, oil and eggs well.
Then add flour, soda and cinnamon.
Then fold in 3 small jars of baby food strained carrots.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 3 round pans.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together. Bring to boil and cook exactly 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Stir well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper. Bake at 350°. Let set until cold. Can add nuts or coconut, if desired.

title: mammaw's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix Wesson oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour a little at a time, soda, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Mix well, then add apples.
You may add some of the apples to mixture before adding all of the flour to moisten batter.
Bake at 300 or 325° for 35-40 minutes in two 8 or 9 inch pans.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in small dish of sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: alice springs chicken grill
directions: Coat chicken in cheese and leek soup.
Grill or barbecue on medium heat, basting with a little oil while cooking.
Blend remaining soup with milk and mushrooms. Stir until boiling and serve over cooked chicken.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Drain and mix beans together. Add beans to browned mixture.
Add brown sugar, mustard, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Put sliced squash in large kettle. Add onions. Mix together in a bowl the vinegar, mustard, turmeric, celery seed, sugar, salt and alum. Pour over squash and bring to a boil.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: cookies 'n cream cheesecake
directions: Place 30 cookies in food processor; finely grind.
Add melted margarine; mix well.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer until well blended.
Add eggs until blended.
Gently stir in 1 1/2 cups of chopped cookies. Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining chopped cookies.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: dinosaur bones
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast the almonds on a cookie sheet until golden, about 6 minutes. Cool slightly. Turn off oven and set nuts aside.

title: shish-ka-bobs
directions: Have thin green stick skewers or regular metal skewers for each person.
Put vegetables and meats out for each person to choose.
Have onion salt and pepper available.
Also a brush and barbecue sauce.
Everyone makes his own and cooks to desired doneness over hot coals.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix string beans, milk, soup and 3/4 cup onions.
Bake in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining 3/4 cup of onions and bake 5 minutes.

title: strawberry spread
directions: Combine ingredients and use as a spread for quick breads and bagels. Refrigerate. This will keep for 3 days. Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix well and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with confectioners sugar. When cool, cut in small squares.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and applesauce.
Sift together baking soda, flour, salt, allspice, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and beat well.
Then add nuts and raisins.
Drop from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Add browned hamburger to spaghetti sauce in large bowl.
Place layer of sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of uncooked noodles, pushing lightly into sauce.
Add
another layer of sauce followed by Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce. Add second layer of noodles, pressing lightly into sauce and continue with above layers until pan is full.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add oleo, melted.
Add all other ingredients. Bake in unbaked pie crust at 350° until almost firm.

title: baked beans
directions: Place hot dogs, onion, bell pepper and 1/2 cup water in a skillet.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Add beans, garlic powder, salt, pepper, sauce, mustard and syrup.
Cook until beans are done.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Stir together; drop by teaspoon on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In saucepan, stir sugar, cornstarch and flour.
Add milk. Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thick and bubbly. Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat. Stir half of mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Return all to saucepan.
Bring to gentle boil, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Pour in baked pie shell and let cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: charlotte's broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix, sugar and salt. Beat eggs and add milk. Combine milk/egg mixture with cornbread mix. Mix well. Add cheese, onion and broccoli. Melt margarine. Pour about 2/3 of margarine in mixture and pour the rest in a pan (I use Corning Ware small square dish 8 x 8). Put mixture in pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes until done.

title: veggie spirelli salad
directions: Combine onion and vinegar and let stand for a few minutes. Then add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and paprika and mix well.
Mix drained veggie spirelli, tomatoes, green pepper and olives.
Pour mix over spirelli and toss lightly.
Cook spirelli 2 or 3 minutes less than package recommends.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and zucchini.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, salt and soda.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1` hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 mixture in greased 8 X 8 X 2 inch pan.
Cover with green chili and monterey jack cheese.
Spread remaining batter over top.
Bake at 400 for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Steam head of cabbage, about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Cut or shred in small pieces.
Alternate layers of cabbage with cream cheese. Add salt and pepper.
Pour half and half or coffee cream over this. Sprinkle cracker crumbs which have been mixed with butter over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: very veggie salad
directions: Bring 2 qt. water to boil in saucepot.
Add veggies and cook 2 minutes, drain and rinse in cold water.
In bowl, combine veggies, red pepper cut in 1/2 inch squares, onion, vinegar and seasoning. Toss and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Using hands, mix all ingredients together well. Roll into bite-sized balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Makes about 250 balls.

title: mrs. woodward's tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
